  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Judges Ahaziah'
      title: God Judges Ahaziah
      number: 1
      content: Moab rebelled against Israel after the death of Ahab.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Ahaziah fell through the lattice of his upper room in Samaria,
        and was injured; so he sent messengers and said to them, \u201CGo, inquire
        of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron, whether I shall recover from this injury.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the angel of the Lord said to Elijah the Tishbite, \u201CArise,
        go up to meet the messengers of the king of Samaria, and say to them, \u2018Is 
        it because there  is no God in Israel that you are going to inquire of Baal-Zebub,
        the god of Ekron?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now therefore, thus says the Lord: \u2018You shall not come down
        from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.\u2019 \u201D
        So Elijah departed."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when the messengers returned to him, he said to them, \u201CWhy
        have you come back?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CA man came up to meet us, and said to
        us, \u2018Go, return to the king who sent you, and say to him, \u201CThus
        says the Lord: \u2018Is  it because there  is no God in Israel that you are
        sending to inquire of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron? Therefore you shall not
        come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.\u2019
        \u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CWhat kind of man was  it who came up
        to meet you and told you these words?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So they answered him, \u201CA hairy man wearing a leather belt around
        his waist.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CIt is Elijah the Tishbite.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king sent to him a captain of fifty with his fifty men.
        So he went up to him; and there he was, sitting on the top of a hill. And
        he spoke to him: \u201CMan of God, the king has said, \u2018Come down!\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Elijah answered and said to the captain of fifty, \u201CIf I am
        a man of God, then let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your
        fifty men.\u201D And fire came down from heaven and consumed him and his
        fifty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then he sent to him another captain of fifty with his fifty men.And
        he answered and said to him: \u201CMan of God, thus has the king said, \u2018Come
        down quickly!\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Elijah answered and said to them, \u201CIf I am a man of God,
        let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty men.\u201D
        And the fire of God came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Again, he sent a third captain of fifty with his fifty men. And the
        third captain of fifty went up, and came and fell on his knees before Elijah,
        and pleaded with him, and said to him: \u201CMan of God, please let my life
        and the life of these fifty servants of yours be precious in your sight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Look, fire has come down from heaven and burned up the first two
        captains of fifties with their fifties. But let my life now be precious in
        your sight.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the angel of the Lord said to Elijah, \u201CGo down with him;
        do not be afraid of him.\u201D So he arose and went down with him to the
        king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Because you
        have sent messengers to inquire of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron, is  it because
        there  is no God in Israel to inquire of His word? Therefore you shall not
        come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So Ahaziah died according to the word of the Lord which Elijah had
        spoken. Because he had no son, Jehoram became king in his place, in the second
        year of Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Ahaziah which he did, are they not written
        in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Ascends to Heaven'
      title: Elijah Ascends to Heaven
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the Lord was about to take up Elijah into
        heaven by a whirlwind, that Elijah went with Elisha from Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Elijah said to Elisha, \u201CStay here, please, for the Lord
        has sent me on to Bethel.\u201DBut Elisha said, \u201CAs the Lord lives,
        and as your soul lives, I will not leave you!\u201D So they went down to
        Bethel."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now the sons of the prophets who were at Bethel came out to Elisha,
        and said to him, \u201CDo you know that the Lord will take away your master
        from over you today?\u201DAnd he said, \u201CYes, I know; keep silent!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Elijah said to him, \u201CElisha, stay here, please, for the
        Lord has sent me on to Jericho.\u201DBut he said, \u201CAs the Lord lives,
        and as your soul lives, I will not leave you!\u201D So they came to Jericho."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now the sons of the prophets who were at Jericho came to Elisha and
        said to him, \u201CDo you know that the Lord will take away your master from
        over you today?\u201DSo he answered, \u201CYes, I know; keep silent!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Elijah said to him, \u201CStay here, please, for the Lord has
        sent me on to the Jordan.\u201DBut he said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, and
        as your soul lives, I will not leave you!\u201D So the two of them went on. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And fifty men of the sons of the prophets went and stood facing them
        at a distance, while the two of them stood by the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Now Elijah took his mantle, rolled it up, and struck the water; and
        it was divided this way and that, so that the two of them crossed over on
        dry ground.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And so it was, when they had crossed over, that Elijah said to Elisha,
        \u201CAsk! What may I do for you, before I am taken away from you?\u201DElisha
        said, \u201CPlease let a double portion of your spirit be upon me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So he said, \u201CYou have asked a hard thing. Nevertheless, if you
        see me when  I  am taken from you, it shall be so for you; but if not, it
        shall not be so.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Then it happened, as they continued on and talked, that suddenly a
        chariot of fire appeared with horses of fire, and separated the two of them;
        and Elijah went up by a whirlwind into heaven.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Elisha saw it, and he cried out, \u201CMy father, my father,
        the chariot of Israel and its horsemen!\u201D So he saw him no more. And
        he took hold of his own clothes and tore them into two pieces. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He also took up the mantle of Elijah that had fallen from him, and
        went back and stood by the bank of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he took the mantle of Elijah that had fallen from him, and struck
        the water, and said, \u201CWhere is the Lord God of Elijah?\u201D And when
        he also had struck the water, it was divided this way and that; and Elisha
        crossed over."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now when the sons of the prophets who were  from Jericho saw him,
        they said, \u201CThe spirit of Elijah rests on Elisha.\u201D And they came
        to meet him, and bowed to the ground before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CLook now, there are fifty strong men
        with your servants. Please let them go and search for your master, lest perhaps
        the Spirit of the Lord has taken him up and cast him upon some mountain or
        into some valley.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CYou shall not send anyone.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But when they urged him till he was ashamed, he said, \u201CSend
        them!\u201D Therefore they sent fifty men, and they searched for three days
        but did not find him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Elisha Performs Miracles'
      title: Elisha Performs Miracles
      number: 18
      content: "And when they came back to him, for he had stayed in Jericho, he
        said to them, \u201CDid I not say to you, \u2018Do not go\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the men of the city said to Elisha, \u201CPlease notice, the
        situation of this city is pleasant, as my lord sees; but the water is bad,
        and the ground barren.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said, \u201CBring me a new bowl, and put salt in it.\u201D
        So they brought it to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he went out to the source of the water, and cast in the salt
        there, and said, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018I have healed this water;
        from it there shall be no more death or barrenness.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So the water remains healed to this day, according to the word of
        Elisha which he spoke.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then he went up from there to Bethel; and as he was going up the
        road, some youths came from the city and mocked him, and said to him, \u201CGo
        up, you baldhead! Go up, you baldhead!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So he turned around and looked at them, and pronounced a curse on
        them in the name of the Lord. And two female bears came out of the woods
        and mauled forty-two of the youths.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Then he went from there to Mount Carmel, and from there he returned
        to Samaria.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moab Rebels Against Israel'
      title: Moab Rebels Against Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Jehoram the son of Ahab became king over Israel at Samaria in
        the eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and reigned twelve years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, but not like his father
        and mother; for he put away the sacred pillar of Baal that his father had
        made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Nevertheless he persisted in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat,
        who had made Israel sin; he did not depart from them.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Mesha king of Moab was a sheepbreeder, and he regularly paid
        the king of Israel one hundred thousand lambs and the wool of one hundred
        thousand rams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But it happened, when Ahab died, that the king of Moab rebelled against
        the king of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So King Jehoram went out of Samaria at that time and mustered all
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he went and sent to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, saying, \u201CThe
        king of Moab has rebelled against me. Will you go with me to fight against
        Moab?\u201DAnd he said, \u201CI will go up; I am as you are, my people as
        your people, my horses as your horses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhich way shall we go up?\u201DAnd he answered,
        \u201CBy way of the Wilderness of Edom.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the king of Israel went with the king of Judah and the king of
        Edom, and they marched on that roundabout route seven days; and there was
        no water for the army, nor for the animals that followed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the king of Israel said, \u201CAlas! For the Lord has called
        these three kings together to deliver them into the hand of Moab.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Jehoshaphat said, \u201CIs  there no prophet of the Lord here,
        that we may inquire of the Lord by him?\u201DSo one of the servants of the
        king of Israel answered and said, \u201CElisha the son of Shaphat is here,
        who poured water on the hands of Elijah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Jehoshaphat said, \u201CThe word of the Lord is with him.\u201D
        So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat and the king of Edom went down to him."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Elisha said to the king of Israel, \u201CWhat have I to do with
        you? Go to the prophets of your father and the prophets of your mother.\u201DBut
        the king of Israel said to him, \u201CNo, for the Lord has called these three
        kings together to deliver them into the hand of Moab.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Elisha said, \u201CAs the Lord of hosts lives, before whom I
        stand, surely were it not that I regard the presence of Jehoshaphat king
        of Judah, I would not look at you, nor see you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But now bring me a musician.\u201DThen it happened, when the musician
        played, that the hand of the Lord came upon him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Make this valley full
        of ditches.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For thus says the Lord: \u2018You shall not see wind, nor shall you
        see rain; yet that valley shall be filled with water, so that you, your cattle,
        and your animals may drink.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And this is a simple matter in the sight of the Lord; He will also
        deliver the Moabites into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Also you shall attack every fortified city and every choice city,
        and shall cut down every good tree, and stop up every spring of water, and
        ruin every good piece of land with stones.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Now it happened in the morning, when the grain offering was offered,
        that suddenly water came by way of Edom, and the land was filled with water.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when all the Moabites heard that the kings had come up to fight
        against them, all who were able to bear arms and older were gathered; and
        they stood at the border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then they rose up early in the morning, and the sun was shining on
        the water; and the Moabites saw the water on the other side as red as blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And they said, \u201CThis is blood; the kings have surely struck
        swords and have killed one another; now therefore, Moab, to the spoil!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So when they came to the camp of Israel, Israel rose up and attacked
        the Moabites, so that they fled before them; and they entered their land,
        killing the Moabites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Then they destroyed the cities, and each man threw a stone on every
        good piece of land and filled it; and they stopped up all the springs of
        water and cut down all the good trees. But they left the stones of Kir Haraseth
        intact. However the slingers surrounded and attacked it.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And when the king of Moab saw that the battle was too fierce for
        him, he took with him seven hundred men who drew swords, to break through
        to the king of Edom, but they could not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then he took his eldest son who would have reigned in his place, and
        offered him as a burnt offering upon the wall; and there was great indignation
        against Israel. So they departed from him and returned to their  own land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elisha and the Widow\u2019s Oil"
      title: "Elisha and the Widow\u2019s Oil"
      number: 1
      content: "A certain woman of the wives of the sons of the prophets cried out
        to Elisha, saying, \u201CYour servant my husband is dead, and you know that
        your servant feared the Lord. And the creditor is coming to take my two sons
        to be his slaves.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Elisha said to her, \u201CWhat shall I do for you? Tell me, what
        do you have in the house?\u201D And she said, \u201CYour maidservant has
        nothing in the house but a jar of oil.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said, \u201CGo, borrow vessels from everywhere, from all
        your neighbors\u2014empty vessels; do not gather just a few. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when you have come in, you shall shut the door behind you and
        your sons; then pour it into all those vessels, and set aside the full ones.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So she went from him and shut the door behind her and her sons, who
        brought the  vessels to her; and she poured it out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now it came to pass, when the vessels were full, that she said to
        her son, \u201CBring me another vessel.\u201DAnd he said to her, \u201CThere 
        is not another vessel.\u201D So the oil ceased. "
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Elisha Raises the Shunammite\u2019s Son"
      title: "Elisha Raises the Shunammite\u2019s Son"
      number: 7
      content: "Then she came and told the man of God. And he said, \u201CGo, sell
        the oil and pay your debt; and you and your sons live on the rest.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now it happened one day that Elisha went to Shunem, where there was
        a notable woman, and she persuaded him to eat some food. So it was, as often
        as he passed by, he would turn in there to eat some food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And she said to her husband, \u201CLook now, I know that this is
        a holy man of God, who passes by us regularly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Please, let us make a small upper room on the wall; and let us put
        a bed for him there, and a table and a chair and a lampstand; so it will
        be, whenever he comes to us, he can turn in there.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it happened one day that he came there, and he turned in to the
        upper room and lay down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he said to Gehazi his servant, \u201CCall this Shunammite woman.\u201D
        When he had called her, she stood before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CSay now to her, \u2018Look, you have been
        concerned for us with all this care. What can  I do for you? Do you want
        me to speak on your behalf to the king or to the commander of the army?\u2019
        \u201DShe answered, \u201CI dwell among my own people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he said, \u201CWhat then is to be done for her?\u201DAnd Gehazi
        answered, \u201CActually, she has no son, and her husband is old.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So he said, \u201CCall her.\u201D When he had called her, she stood
        in the doorway. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said, \u201CAbout this time next year you shall embrace a
        son.\u201DAnd she said, \u201CNo, my lord. Man of God, do not lie to your
        maidservant!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But the woman conceived, and bore a son when the appointed time had
        come, of which Elisha had told her.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the child grew. Now it happened one day that he went out to his
        father, to the reapers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said to his father, \u201CMy head, my head!\u201DSo he said
        to a servant, \u201CCarry him to his mother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When he had taken him and brought him to his mother, he sat on her
        knees till noon, and then died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And she went up and laid him on the bed of the man of God, shut the 
        door upon him, and went out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then she called to her husband, and said, \u201CPlease send me one
        of the young men and one of the donkeys, that I may run to the man of God
        and come back.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So he said, \u201CWhy are you going to him today? It  is neither
        the New Moon nor the Sabbath.\u201DAnd she said, \u201CIt  is well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then she saddled a donkey, and said to her servant, \u201CDrive,
        and go forward; do not slacken the pace for me unless I tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And so she departed, and went to the man of God at Mount Carmel.So
        it was, when the man of God saw her afar off, that he said to his servant
        Gehazi, \u201CLook, the Shunammite woman! "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Please run now to meet her, and say to her, \u2018Is  it well with
        you? Is  it well with your husband? Is  it well with the child?\u2019 \u201DAnd
        she answered, \u201CIt  is well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Now when she came to the man of God at the hill, she caught him by
        the feet, but Gehazi came near to push her away. But the man of God said,
        \u201CLet her alone; for her soul is in deep distress, and the Lord has hidden
        it from me, and has not told me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So she said, \u201CDid I ask a son of my lord? Did I not say, \u2018Do
        not deceive me\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he said to Gehazi, \u201CGet yourself ready, and take my staff
        in your hand, and be on your way. If you meet anyone, do not greet him; and
        if anyone greets you, do not answer him; but lay my staff on the face of
        the child.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And the mother of the child said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, and as
        your soul lives, I will not leave you.\u201D So he arose and followed her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Now Gehazi went on ahead of them, and laid the staff on the face
        of the child; but there  was neither voice nor hearing. Therefore he went
        back to meet him, and told him, saying, \u201CThe child has not awakened.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When Elisha came into the house, there was the child, lying dead
        on his bed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He went in therefore, shut the door behind the two of them, and prayed
        to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And he went up and lay on the child, and put his mouth on his mouth,
        his eyes on his eyes, and his hands on his hands; and he stretched himself
        out on the child, and the flesh of the child became warm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'He returned and walked back and forth in the house, and again went
        up and stretched himself out on him; then the child sneezed seven times,
        and the child opened his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And he called Gehazi and said, \u201CCall this Shunammite woman.\u201D
        So he called her. And when she came in to him, he said, \u201CPick up your
        son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Elisha Purifies the Pot of Stew'
      title: Elisha Purifies the Pot of Stew
      number: 37
      content: So she went in, fell at his feet, and bowed to the ground; then she
        picked up her son and went out.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Elisha returned to Gilgal, and there  was a famine in the land.
        Now the sons of the prophets were  sitting before him; and he said to his
        servant, \u201CPut on the large pot, and boil stew for the sons of the prophets.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So one went out into the field to gather herbs, and found a wild
        vine, and gathered from it a lapful of wild gourds, and came and sliced them
        into the pot of stew, though they did not know what  they  were.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then they served it to the men to eat. Now it happened, as they were
        eating the stew, that they cried out and said, \u201CMan of God, there  is 
        death in the pot!\u201D And they could not eat it."
      comments: []
    - name: '41: Elisha Feeds One Hundred Men'
      title: Elisha Feeds One Hundred Men
      number: 41
      content: "So he said, \u201CThen bring some flour.\u201D And he put it into
        the pot, and said, \u201CServe it to the people, that they may eat.\u201D
        And there was nothing harmful in the pot."
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then a man came from Baal Shalisha, and brought the man of God bread
        of the firstfruits, twenty loaves of barley bread, and newly ripened grain
        in his knapsack. And he said, \u201CGive it to the people, that they may
        eat.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "But his servant said, \u201CWhat? Shall I set this before one hundred
        men?\u201DHe said again, \u201CGive it to the people, that they may eat;
        for thus says the Lord: \u2018They shall eat and have some left over.\u2019
        \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: So he set it before them; and they ate and had some left over, according
        to the word of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Naaman\u2019s Leprosy Healed"
      title: "Naaman\u2019s Leprosy Healed"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Naaman, commander of the army of the king of Syria, was a great
        and honorable man in the eyes of his master, because by him the Lord had
        given victory to Syria. He was also a mighty man of valor, but a leper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Syrians had gone out on raids, and had brought back captive
        a young girl from the land of Israel. She waited on Naaman\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then she said to her mistress, \u201CIf only my master were with
        the prophet who is in Samaria! For he would heal him of his leprosy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Naaman went in and told his master, saying, \u201CThus and thus
        said the girl who is from the land of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the king of Syria said, \u201CGo now, and I will send a letter
        to the king of Israel.\u201DSo he departed and took with him ten talents
        of silver, six thousand shekels of gold, and ten changes of clothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Then he brought the letter to the king of Israel, which said,Now be
        advised, when this letter comes to you, that I have sent Naaman my servant
        to you, that you may heal him of his leprosy.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And it happened, when the king of Israel read the letter, that he
        tore his clothes and said, \u201CAm I God, to kill and make alive, that this
        man sends a man to me to heal him of his leprosy? Therefore please consider,
        and see how he seeks a quarrel with me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So it was, when Elisha the man of God heard that the king of Israel
        had torn his clothes, that he sent to the king, saying, \u201CWhy have you
        torn your clothes? Please let him come to me, and he shall know that there
        is a prophet in Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Naaman went with his horses and chariot, and he stood at the
        door of Elisha\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Elisha sent a messenger to him, saying, \u201CGo and wash in
        the Jordan seven times, and your flesh shall be restored to you, and you 
        shall be clean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Naaman became furious, and went away and said, \u201CIndeed,
        I said to myself, \u2018He will surely come out to  me, and stand and call
        on the name of the Lord his God, and wave his hand over the place, and heal
        the leprosy.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Are not the Abanah and the Pharpar, the rivers of Damascus, better
        than all the waters of Israel? Could I not wash in them and be clean?\u201D
        So he turned and went away in a rage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And his servants came near and spoke to him, and said, \u201CMy father,
        if the prophet had told you to  do something great, would you not have done
        it? How much more then, when he says to you, \u2018Wash, and be clean\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So he went down and dipped seven times in the Jordan, according to
        the saying of the man of God; and his flesh was restored like the flesh of
        a little child, and he was clean.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he returned to the man of God, he and all his aides, and came
        and stood before him; and he said, \u201CIndeed, now I know that there  is 
        no God in all the earth, except in Israel; now therefore, please take a gift
        from your servant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But he said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, before whom I stand, I will
        receive nothing.\u201D And he urged him to take it, but he refused."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Naaman said, \u201CThen, if not, please let your servant be given
        two mule-loads of earth; for your servant will no longer offer either burnt
        offering or sacrifice to other gods, but to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Yet in this thing may the Lord pardon your servant: when my master
        goes into the temple of Rimmon to worship there, and he leans on my hand,
        and I bow down in the temple of Rimmon\u2014when I bow down in the temple
        of Rimmon, may the Lord please pardon your servant in this thing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Gehazi\u2019s Greed"
      title: "Gehazi\u2019s Greed"
      number: 19
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CGo in peace.\u201D So he departed from
        him a short distance."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Gehazi, the servant of Elisha the man of God, said, \u201CLook,
        my master has spared Naaman this Syrian, while not receiving from his hands
        what he brought; but as the Lord lives, I will run after him and take something
        from him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So Gehazi pursued Naaman. When Naaman saw him running after him,
        he got down from the chariot to meet him, and said, \u201CIs all well?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he said, \u201CAll is  well. My master has sent me, saying, \u2018Indeed,
        just now two young men of the sons of the prophets have come to me from the
        mountains of Ephraim. Please give them a talent of silver and two changes
        of garments.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Naaman said, \u201CPlease, take two talents.\u201D And he urged
        him, and bound two talents of silver in two bags, with two changes of garments,
        and handed them to two of his servants; and they carried them on ahead of
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When he came to the citadel, he took them from their hand, and stored
        them away in the house; then he let the men go, and they departed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now he went in and stood before his master. Elisha said to him, \u201CWhere
        did  you  go, Gehazi?\u201DAnd he said, \u201CYour servant did not go anywhere.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CDid not my heart go with  you when the
        man turned back from his chariot to meet you? Is  it  time to receive money
        and to receive clothing, olive groves and vineyards, sheep and oxen, male
        and female servants? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore the leprosy of Naaman shall cling to you and your descendants
        forever.\u201D And he went out from his presence leprous, as  white as snow."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Floating Ax Head'
      title: The Floating Ax Head
      number: 1
      content: "And the sons of the prophets said to Elisha, \u201CSee now, the place
        where we dwell with you is too small for us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Please, let us go to the Jordan, and let every man take a beam from
        there, and let us make there a place where we may dwell.\u201DSo he answered,
        \u201CGo.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then one said, \u201CPlease consent to go with your servants.\u201DAnd
        he answered, \u201CI will go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So he went with them. And when they came to the Jordan, they cut
        down trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But as one was cutting down a tree, the iron ax  head fell into the
        water; and he cried out and said, \u201CAlas, master! For it was borrowed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the man of God said, \u201CWhere did it fall?\u201D And he showed
        him the place. So he cut off a stick, and threw it in there; and he made
        the iron float. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Blinded Syrians Captured'
      title: The Blinded Syrians Captured
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore he said, \u201CPick it up for yourself.\u201D So he reached
        out his hand and took it."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now the king of Syria was making war against Israel; and he consulted
        with his servants, saying, \u201CMy camp will  be in such and such a place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the man of God sent to the king of Israel, saying, \u201CBeware
        that you do not pass this place, for the Syrians are coming down there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then the king of Israel sent someone to the place of which the man
        of God had told him. Thus he warned him, and he was watchful there, not just
        once or twice.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore the heart of the king of Syria was greatly troubled by
        this thing; and he called his servants and said to them, \u201CWill you not
        show me which of us is for the king of Israel?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And one of his servants said, \u201CNone, my lord, O king; but Elisha,
        the prophet who is in Israel, tells the king of Israel the words that you
        speak in your bedroom.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So he said, \u201CGo and see where he is, that I may send and get
        him.\u201DAnd it was told him, saying, \u201CSurely he  is in Dothan.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore he sent horses and chariots and a great army there, and
        they came by night and surrounded the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when the servant of the man of God arose early and went out,
        there was an army, surrounding the city with horses and chariots. And his
        servant said to him, \u201CAlas, my master! What shall we do?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So he answered, \u201CDo not fear, for those who are with us are
        more than those who are with them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Elisha prayed, and said, \u201CLord, I pray, open his eyes that
        he may see.\u201D Then the Lord  opened the eyes of the young man, and he
        saw. And behold, the mountain was full of horses and chariots of fire all
        around Elisha. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So when the  Syrians came down to him, Elisha prayed to the Lord,
        and said, \u201CStrike this people, I pray, with blindness.\u201D And He
        struck them with blindness according to the word of Elisha."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now Elisha said to them, \u201CThis is not the way, nor is this the
        city. Follow me, and I will bring you to the man whom you seek.\u201D But
        he led them to Samaria."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So it was, when they had come to Samaria, that Elisha said, \u201CLord,
        open the eyes of these men, that they may see.\u201D And the Lord opened
        their eyes, and they saw; and there they  were, inside Samaria!"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now when the king of Israel saw them, he said to Elisha, \u201CMy
        father, shall I kill them? Shall I kill them?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But he answered, \u201CYou shall not kill them. Would you kill those
        whom you have taken captive with your sword and your bow? Set food and water
        before them, that they may eat and drink and go to their master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Syria Besieges Samaria in Famine'
      title: Syria Besieges Samaria in Famine
      number: 23
      content: Then he prepared a great feast for them; and after they ate and drank,
        he sent them away and they went to their master. So the bands of Syrian raiders
        came no more into the land of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And it happened after this that Ben-Hadad king of Syria gathered
        all his army, and went up and besieged Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And there was a great famine in Samaria; and indeed they besieged
        it until a donkey\u2019s head was sold for eighty shekels of silver, and
        one-fourth of a kab of dove droppings for five shekels of silver."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then, as the king of Israel was passing by on the wall, a woman cried
        out to him, saying, \u201CHelp, my lord, O king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he said, \u201CIf the Lord does not help you, where can I find
        help for you? From the threshing floor or from the winepress?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the king said to her, \u201CWhat is troubling you?\u201DAnd
        she answered, \u201CThis woman said to me, \u2018Give your son, that we may
        eat him today, and we will eat my son tomorrow.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So we boiled my son, and ate him. And I said to her on the next day,
        \u2018Give your son, that we may eat him\u2019; but she has hidden her son.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now it happened, when the king heard the words of the woman, that
        he tore his clothes; and as he passed by on the wall, the people looked,
        and there underneath he  had sackcloth on his body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he said, \u201CGod do so to me and more also, if the head of
        Elisha the son of Shaphat remains on him today!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But Elisha was sitting in his house, and the elders were sitting
        with him. And the  king sent a man ahead of him, but before the messenger
        came to him, he said to the elders, \u201CDo you see how this son of a murderer
        has sent someone to take away my head? Look, when the messenger comes, shut
        the door, and hold him fast at the door. Is not the sound of his master\u2019s
        feet behind him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And while he was still talking with them, there was the messenger,
        coming down to him; and then the  king said, \u201CSurely this calamity is
        from the Lord; why should I wait for the Lord any longer?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Then Elisha said, \u201CHear the word of the Lord. Thus says the
        Lord: \u2018Tomorrow about this time a seah of fine flour shall  be  sold
        for a shekel, and two seahs of barley for a shekel, at the gate of Samaria.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: The Syrians Flee'
      title: The Syrians Flee
      number: 2
      content: "So an officer on whose hand the king leaned answered the man of God
        and said, \u201CLook, if the Lord would make windows in heaven, could this
        thing be?\u201DAnd he said, \u201CIn fact, you shall see it with your eyes,
        but you shall not eat of it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now there were four leprous men at the entrance of the gate; and
        they said to one another, \u201CWhy are we sitting here until we die? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "If we say, \u2018We will enter the city,\u2019 the famine is in the
        city, and we shall die there. And if we sit here, we die also. Now therefore,
        come, let us surrender to the army of the Syrians. If they keep us alive,
        we shall live; and if they kill us, we shall only die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And they rose at twilight to go to the camp of the Syrians; and when
        they had come to the outskirts of the Syrian camp, to their surprise no one
        was there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord had caused the army of the Syrians to hear the noise
        of chariots and the noise of horses\u2014the noise of a great army; so they
        said to one another, \u201CLook, the king of Israel has hired against us
        the kings of the Hittites and the kings of the Egyptians to attack us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore they arose and fled at twilight, and left the camp intact\u2014their
        tents, their horses, and their donkeys\u2014and they fled for their lives. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And when these lepers came to the outskirts of the camp, they went
        into one tent and ate and drank, and carried from it silver and gold and
        clothing, and went and hid them; then they came back and entered another
        tent, and carried some from there also, and went and hid it.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they said to one another, \u201CWe are not doing right. This
        day is a day of good news, and we remain silent. If we wait until morning
        light, some punishment will come upon us. Now therefore, come, let us go
        and tell the king\u2019s household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they went and called to the gatekeepers of the city, and told
        them, saying, \u201CWe went to the Syrian camp, and surprisingly no one was
        there, not a human sound\u2014only horses and donkeys tied, and the tents
        intact.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the gatekeepers called out, and they told it to the king\u2019s
        household inside."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So the king arose in the night and said to his servants, \u201CLet
        me now tell you what the Syrians have done to us. They know that we are 
        hungry; therefore they have gone out of the camp to hide themselves in the
        field, saying, \u2018When they come out of the city, we shall catch them
        alive, and get into the city.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And one of his servants answered and said, \u201CPlease, let several
        men take five of the remaining horses which are left in the city. Look, they
        may  either  become like all the multitude of Israel that are left in it;
        or indeed, I  say, they may  become like all the multitude of Israel left
        from those who are consumed; so let us send them and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore they took two chariots with horses; and the king sent them
        in the direction of the Syrian army, saying, \u201CGo and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they went after them to the Jordan; and indeed all the road was
        full of garments and weapons which the Syrians had thrown away in their haste.
        So the messengers returned and told the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Then the people went out and plundered the tents of the Syrians. So
        a seah of fine flour was sold for a shekel, and two seahs of barley for a
        shekel, according to the word of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the king had appointed the officer on whose hand he leaned to
        have charge of the gate. But the people trampled him in the gate, and he
        died, just as the man of God had said, who spoke when the king came down
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So it happened just as the man of God had spoken to the king, saying,
        \u201CTwo seahs of barley for a shekel, and a seah of fine flour for a shekel,
        shall be sold tomorrow about this time in the gate of Samaria.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then that officer had answered the man of God, and said, \u201CNow
        look, if the Lord would make windows in heaven, could such a thing be?\u201DAnd
        he had said, \u201CIn fact, you shall see it with your eyes, but you shall
        not eat of it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And so it happened to him, for the people trampled him in the gate,
        and he died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The King Restores the Shunammite\u2019s Land"
      title: "The King Restores the Shunammite\u2019s Land"
      number: 1
      content: "Then Elisha spoke to the woman whose son he had restored to life,
        saying, \u201CArise and go, you and your household, and stay wherever you
        can; for the Lord  has called for a famine, and furthermore, it will come
        upon the land for seven years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So the woman arose and did according to the saying of the man of God,
        and she went with her household and dwelt in the land of the Philistines
        seven years.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It came to pass, at the end of seven years, that the woman returned
        from the land of the Philistines; and she went to make an appeal to the king
        for her house and for her land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king talked with Gehazi, the servant of the man of God,
        saying, \u201CTell me, please, all the great things Elisha has done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now it happened, as he was telling the king how he had restored the
        dead to life, that there was the woman whose son he had restored to life,
        appealing to the king for her house and for her land. And Gehazi said, \u201CMy
        lord, O king, this is the woman, and this is her son whom Elisha restored
        to life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Death of Ben-Hadad'
      title: Death of Ben-Hadad
      number: 6
      content: "And when the king asked the woman, she told him.So the king appointed
        a certain officer for her, saying, \u201CRestore all that was hers, and all
        the proceeds of the field from the day that she left the land until now.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Elisha went to Damascus, and Ben-Hadad king of Syria was sick;
        and it was told him, saying, \u201CThe man of God has come here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the king said to Hazael, \u201CTake a present in your hand, and
        go to meet the man of God, and inquire of the Lord by him, saying, \u2018Shall
        I recover from this disease?\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Hazael went to meet him and took a present with him, of every
        good thing of Damascus, forty camel-loads; and he came and stood before him,
        and said, \u201CYour son Ben-Hadad king of Syria has sent me to you, saying,
        \u2018Shall I recover from this disease?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Elisha said to him, \u201CGo, say to him, \u2018You shall certainly
        recover.\u2019 However the Lord has shown me that he will really die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then he set his countenance in a stare until he was ashamed; and
        the man of God wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Hazael said, \u201CWhy is my lord weeping?\u201DHe answered,
        \u201CBecause I know the evil that you will do to the children of Israel:
        Their strongholds you will set on fire, and their young men you will kill
        with the sword; and you will dash their children, and rip open their women
        with child.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Hazael said, \u201CBut what is your servant\u2014a dog, that he
        should do this gross thing?\u201DAnd Elisha answered, \u201CThe Lord has
        shown me that you will  become king over Syria.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he departed from Elisha, and came to his master, who said to
        him, \u201CWhat did Elisha say to you?\u201D And he answered, \u201CHe told
        me you would surely recover.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jehoram Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoram Reigns in Judah
      number: 15
      content: But it happened on the next day that he took a thick cloth and dipped
        it in water, and spread it over his face so that he died; and Hazael reigned
        in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now in the fifth year of Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, Jehoshaphat
        having  been king of Judah, Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat began to reign
        as king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight
        years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, just as the house
        of Ahab had done, for the daughter of Ahab was his wife; and he did evil
        in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Yet the Lord would not destroy Judah, for the sake of His servant
        David, as He promised him to give a lamp to him and his sons forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In his days Edom revolted against Judah\u2019s authority, and made
        a king over themselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So Joram went to Zair, and all his chariots with him. Then he rose
        by night and attacked the Edomites who had surrounded him and the captains
        of the chariots; and the troops fled to their tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus Edom has been in revolt against Judah\u2019s authority to this
        day. And Libnah revolted at that time."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Joram, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Ahaziah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Ahaziah Reigns in Judah
      number: 24
      content: So Joram rested with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers
        in the City of David. Then Ahaziah his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'In the twelfth year of Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, Ahaziah
        the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Ahaziah was  twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        one year in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Athaliah the granddaughter
        of Omri, king of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And he walked in the way of the house of Ahab, and did evil in the
        sight of the Lord, like the house of Ahab, for he was the son-in-law of the
        house of Ahab.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now he went with Joram the son of Ahab to war against Hazael king
        of Syria at Ramoth Gilead; and the Syrians wounded Joram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Then King Joram went back to Jezreel to recover from the wounds which
        the Syrians had inflicted on him at Ramah, when he fought against Hazael
        king of Syria. And Ahaziah the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, went down to
        see Joram the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was sick.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehu Anointed King of Israel'
      title: Jehu Anointed King of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "And Elisha the prophet called one of the sons of the prophets, and
        said to him, \u201CGet yourself ready, take this flask of oil in your hand,
        and go to Ramoth Gilead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now when you arrive at that place, look there for Jehu the son of
        Jehoshaphat, the son of Nimshi, and go in and make him rise up from among
        his associates, and take him to an inner room. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then take the flask of oil, and pour it on his head, and say, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord: \u201CI have anointed you king over Israel.\u201D \u2019 Then
        open the door and flee, and do not delay.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the young man, the servant of the prophet, went to Ramoth Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when he arrived, there were the captains of the army sitting;
        and he said, \u201CI have a message for you, Commander.\u201DJehu said, \u201CFor
        which one of us?\u201DAnd he said, \u201CFor you, Commander.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he arose and went into the house. And he poured the oil on his
        head, and said to him, \u201CThus says the Lord God of Israel: \u2018I have
        anointed you king over the people of the Lord, over Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You shall strike down the house of Ahab your master, that I may avenge
        the blood of My servants the prophets, and the blood of all the servants
        of the Lord, at the hand of Jezebel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the whole house of Ahab shall perish; and I will cut off from
        Ahab all the males in Israel, both bond and free. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So I will make the house of Ahab like the house of Jeroboam the son
        of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The dogs shall eat Jezebel on the plot of  ground at Jezreel, and
        there  shall  be none to bury her.\u2019 \u201D And he opened the door and
        fled."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Jehu came out to the servants of his master, and one said to
        him, \u201CIs all well? Why did this madman come to you?\u201DAnd he said
        to them, \u201CYou know the man and his babble.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they said, \u201CA lie! Tell us now.\u201DSo he said, \u201CThus
        and thus he spoke to me, saying, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CI have anointed
        you king over Israel.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Joram of Israel Killed'
      title: Joram of Israel Killed
      number: 13
      content: "Then each man hastened to take his garment and put it under him on
        the top of the steps; and they blew trumpets, saying, \u201CJehu is king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat, the son of Nimshi, conspired against
        Joram. (Now Joram had been defending Ramoth Gilead, he and all Israel, against
        Hazael king of Syria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But King Joram had returned to Jezreel to recover from the wounds
        which the Syrians had inflicted on him when he fought with Hazael king of
        Syria.) And Jehu said, \u201CIf you are so minded, let no one leave or escape
        from the city to go and tell it in Jezreel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So Jehu rode in a chariot and went to Jezreel, for Joram was laid
        up there; and Ahaziah king of Judah had come down to see Joram.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now a watchman stood on the tower in Jezreel, and he saw the company
        of Jehu as he came, and said, \u201CI see a company of men.\u201DAnd Joram
        said, \u201CGet a horseman and send him to meet them, and let him say, \u2018Is 
        it peace?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the horseman went to meet him, and said, \u201CThus says the king:
        \u2018Is  it peace?\u2019 \u201DAnd Jehu said, \u201CWhat have you to do
        with peace? Turn around and follow me.\u201DSo the watchman reported, saying,
        \u201CThe messenger went to them, but is not coming back.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he sent out a second horseman who came to them, and said, \u201CThus
        says the king: \u2018Is  it peace?\u2019 \u201DAnd Jehu answered, \u201CWhat
        have you to do with peace? Turn around and follow me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So the watchman reported, saying, \u201CHe went up to them and is
        not coming back; and the driving is like the driving of Jehu the son of Nimshi,
        for he drives furiously!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Joram said, \u201CMake ready.\u201D And his chariot was made
        ready. Then Joram king of Israel and Ahaziah king of Judah went out, each
        in his chariot; and they went out to meet Jehu, and met him on the property
        of Naboth the Jezreelite."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now it happened, when Joram saw Jehu, that he said, \u201CIs  it
        peace, Jehu?\u201DSo he answered, \u201CWhat peace, as long as the harlotries
        of your mother Jezebel and her witchcraft are  so many?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Joram turned around and fled, and said to Ahaziah, \u201CTreachery,
        Ahaziah!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now Jehu drew his bow with full strength and shot Jehoram between
        his arms; and the arrow came out at his heart, and he sank down in his chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Jehu said to Bidkar his captain, \u201CPick him up, and throw
        him into the tract of the field of Naboth the Jezreelite; for remember, when
        you and I were riding together behind Ahab his father, that the Lord laid
        this burden upon him: "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Ahaziah of Judah Killed'
      title: Ahaziah of Judah Killed
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018Surely I saw yesterday the blood of Naboth and the blood of
        his sons,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018and I will repay you in this plot,\u2019
        says the Lord. Now therefore, take and throw him on the plot of  ground,
        according to the word of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But when Ahaziah king of Judah saw this, he fled by the road to Beth
        Haggan. So Jehu pursued him, and said, \u201CShoot him also in the chariot.\u201D
        And  they  shot  him at the Ascent of Gur, which is by Ibleam. Then he fled
        to Megiddo, and died there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And his servants carried him in the chariot to Jerusalem, and buried
        him in his tomb with his fathers in the City of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: "29: Jezebel\u2019s Violent Death"
      title: "Jezebel\u2019s Violent Death"
      number: 29
      content: In the eleventh year of Joram the son of Ahab, Ahaziah had become
        king over Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now when Jehu had come to Jezreel, Jezebel heard of  it;  and she
        put paint on her eyes and adorned her head, and looked through a window. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then, as Jehu entered at the gate, she said, \u201CIs  it peace,
        Zimri, murderer of your master?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And he looked up at the window, and said, \u201CWho is on my side?
        Who?\u201D So two or three eunuchs looked out at him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then he said, \u201CThrow her down.\u201D So they threw her down,
        and some of her blood spattered on the wall and on the horses; and he trampled
        her underfoot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And when he had gone in, he ate and drank. Then he said, \u201CGo
        now, see to this accursed woman, and bury her, for she was a king\u2019s
        daughter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So they went to bury her, but they found no more of her than the
        skull and the feet and the palms of her hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Therefore they came back and told him. And he said, \u201CThis is
        the word of the Lord, which He spoke by His servant Elijah the Tishbite,
        saying, \u2018On the plot of  ground at Jezreel dogs shall eat the flesh
        of Jezebel; "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "and the corpse of Jezebel shall be as refuse on the surface of the
        field, in the plot at Jezreel, so that they shall not say, \u201CHere lies
        Jezebel.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ahab\u2019s Seventy Sons Killed"
      title: "Ahab\u2019s Seventy Sons Killed"
      number: 1
      content: "Now Ahab had seventy sons in Samaria. And Jehu wrote and sent letters
        to Samaria, to the rulers of Jezreel, to the elders, and to those who reared
        Ahab\u2019s sons, saying:"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now as soon as this letter comes to you, since your master\u2019s
        sons are with you, and you have chariots and horses, a fortified city also,
        and weapons, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "choose the best qualified of your master\u2019s sons, set him on
        his father\u2019s throne, and fight for your master\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But they were exceedingly afraid, and said, \u201CLook, two kings
        could not stand up to him; how then can we stand?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he who was in charge of the house, and he who was in charge of
        the city, the elders also, and those who reared the  sons, sent to Jehu,
        saying, \u201CWe are your servants, we will do all you tell us; but we will
        not make anyone king. Do what  is good in your sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he wrote a second letter to them, saying:If you are for me and
        will obey my voice, take the heads of the men, your master\u2019s sons, and
        come to me at Jezreel by this time tomorrow.Now the king\u2019s sons, seventy
        persons, were with the great men of the city, who were rearing them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So it was, when the letter came to them, that they took the king\u2019s
        sons and slaughtered seventy persons, put their heads in baskets and sent
        them to him at Jezreel."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then a messenger came and told him, saying, \u201CThey have brought
        the heads of the king\u2019s sons.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CLay them in two
        heaps at the entrance of the gate until morning.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So it was, in the morning, that he went out and stood, and said to
        all the people, \u201CYou are righteous. Indeed I conspired against my master
        and killed him; but who killed all these? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Know now that nothing shall fall to the earth of the word of the
        Lord which the Lord spoke concerning the house of Ahab; for the Lord has
        done what He spoke by His servant Elijah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Ahaziah\u2019s Forty-two Brothers Killed"
      title: "Ahaziah\u2019s Forty-two Brothers Killed"
      number: 11
      content: So Jehu killed all who remained of the house of Ahab in Jezreel, and
        all his great men and his close acquaintances and his priests, until he left
        him none remaining.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he arose and departed and went to Samaria. On the way, at Beth
        Eked of the Shepherds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jehu met with the brothers of Ahaziah king of Judah, and said, \u201CWho
        are you?\u201DSo they answered, \u201CWe are the brothers of Ahaziah; we
        have come down to greet the sons of the king and the sons of the queen mother.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "14: The Rest of Ahab\u2019s Family Killed"
      title: "The Rest of Ahab\u2019s Family Killed"
      number: 14
      content: "And he said, \u201CTake them alive!\u201D So they took them alive,
        and killed them at the well of Beth Eked, forty-two men; and he left none
        of them."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now when he departed from there, he met Jehonadab the son of Rechab,
        coming to meet him; and he greeted him and said to him, \u201CIs your heart
        right, as my heart is toward your heart?\u201DAnd Jehonadab answered, \u201CIt
        is.\u201DJehu  said, \u201CIf it is, give me your hand.\u201D So he gave
        him his hand, and he took him up to him into the chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said, \u201CCome with me, and see my zeal for the Lord.\u201D
        So they had him ride in his chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Worshipers of Baal Killed'
      title: Worshipers of Baal Killed
      number: 17
      content: And when he came to Samaria, he killed all who remained to Ahab in
        Samaria, till he had destroyed them, according to the word of the Lord  which
        He spoke to Elijah.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jehu gathered all the people together, and said to them, \u201CAhab
        served Baal a little, Jehu will serve him much. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now therefore, call to me all the prophets of Baal, all his servants,
        and all his priests. Let no one be missing, for I have a great sacrifice
        for Baal. Whoever is missing shall not live.\u201D But Jehu acted deceptively,
        with the intent of destroying the worshipers of Baal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Jehu said, \u201CProclaim a solemn assembly for Baal.\u201D So
        they proclaimed it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Jehu sent throughout all Israel; and all the worshipers of Baal
        came, so that there was not a man left who did not come. So they came into
        the temple of Baal, and the temple of Baal was full from one end to the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he said to the one in charge of the wardrobe, \u201CBring out
        vestments for all the worshipers of Baal.\u201D So he brought out vestments
        for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Jehu and Jehonadab the son of Rechab went into the temple of
        Baal, and said to the worshipers of Baal, \u201CSearch and see that no servants
        of the Lord are here with you, but only the worshipers of Baal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So they went in to offer sacrifices and burnt offerings. Now Jehu
        had appointed for himself eighty men on the outside, and had said, \u201CIf
        any of the men whom I have brought into your hands escapes, whoever  lets 
        him  escape, it shall be  his life for the life of the other.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now it happened, as soon as he had made an end of offering the burnt
        offering, that Jehu said to the guard and to the captains, \u201CGo in and
        kill them; let no one come out!\u201D And they killed them with the edge
        of the sword; then the guards and the officers threw them out, and went into
        the inner room of the temple of Baal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And they brought the sacred pillars out of the temple of Baal and
        burned them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then they broke down the sacred pillar of Baal, and tore down the
        temple of Baal and made it a refuse dump to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Thus Jehu destroyed Baal from Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'However Jehu did not turn away from the sins of Jeroboam the son
        of Nebat, who had made Israel sin, that  is, from the golden calves that
        were at Bethel and Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And the Lord  said to Jehu, \u201CBecause you have done well in doing
        what  is right in My sight, and have done to the house of Ahab all that was
        in My heart, your sons shall sit on the throne of Israel to the fourth generation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Death of Jehu'
      title: Death of Jehu
      number: 31
      content: But Jehu took no heed to walk in the law of the Lord God of Israel
        with all his heart; for he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam, who
        had made Israel sin.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In those days the Lord began to cut off parts of Israel; and Hazael
        conquered them in all the territory of Israel '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "from the Jordan eastward: all the land of Gilead\u2014Gad, Reuben,
        and Manasseh\u2014from Aroer, which is by the River Arnon, including Gilead
        and Bashan."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehu, all that he did, and all his might,
        are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So Jehu rested with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria.
        Then Jehoahaz his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: And the period that Jehu reigned over Israel in Samaria was twenty-eight
        years.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Athaliah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Athaliah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'When Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she
        arose and destroyed all the royal heirs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Jehosheba, the daughter of King Joram, sister of Ahaziah, took
        Joash the son of Ahaziah, and stole him away from among the king\u2019s sons
        who  were being murdered; and they hid him and his nurse in the bedroom,
        from Athaliah, so that he was not killed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Joash Crowned King of Judah'
      title: Joash Crowned King of Judah
      number: 3
      content: So he was hidden with her in the house of the Lord for six years,
        while Athaliah reigned over the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "In the seventh year Jehoiada sent and brought the captains of hundreds\u2014of
        the bodyguards and the escorts\u2014and brought them into the house of the
        Lord to him. And he made a covenant with them and took an oath from them
        in the house of the Lord, and showed them the king\u2019s son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he commanded them, saying, \u201CThis is what you shall do:
        one-third of you who come on duty on the Sabbath shall be keeping watch over
        the king\u2019s house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'one-third shall  be at the gate of Sur, and one-third at the gate
        behind the escorts. You shall keep the watch of the house, lest it be broken
        down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The two contingents of you who go off duty on the Sabbath shall keep
        the watch of the house of the Lord for the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But you shall surround the king on all sides, every man with his
        weapons in his hand; and whoever comes within range, let him be put to death.
        You are to be with the king as he goes out and as he comes in.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the captains of the hundreds did according to all that Jehoiada
        the priest commanded. Each of them took his men who were to be on duty on
        the Sabbath, with those who were going off duty on the Sabbath, and came
        to Jehoiada the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the priest gave the captains of hundreds the spears and shields
        which had  belonged to King David, that were in the temple of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the escorts stood, every man with his weapons in his hand, all
        around the king, from the right side of the temple to the left side of the
        temple, by the altar and the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Death of Athaliah'
      title: Death of Athaliah
      number: 12
      content: "And he brought out the king\u2019s son, put the crown on him, and
        gave  him the Testimony; they made him king and anointed him, and they clapped
        their hands and said, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when Athaliah heard the noise of the escorts and the people,
        she came to the people in the temple of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When she looked, there was the king standing by a pillar according
        to custom; and the leaders and the trumpeters were by the king. All the people
        of the land were rejoicing and blowing trumpets. So Athaliah tore her clothes
        and cried out, \u201CTreason! Treason!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Jehoiada the priest commanded the captains of the hundreds, the
        officers of the army, and said to them, \u201CTake her outside under guard,
        and slay with the sword whoever follows her.\u201D For the priest had said,
        \u201CDo not let her be killed in the house of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they seized her; and she went by way of the horses\u2019 entrance
        into the king\u2019s house, and there she was killed."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jehoiada made a covenant between the Lord, the king, and the
        people, that they should be the Lord\u2019s people, and also  between the
        king and the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And all the people of the land went to the temple of Baal, and tore
        it down. They thoroughly broke in pieces its altars and images, and killed
        Mattan the priest of Baal before the altars. And the priest appointed officers
        over the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he took the captains of hundreds, the bodyguards, the escorts,
        and all the people of the land; and they brought the king down from the house
        of the Lord, and went by way of the gate of the escorts to the king\u2019s
        house. Then he sat on the throne of the kings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So all the people of the land rejoiced; and the city was quiet, for
        they had slain Athaliah with the sword in the king\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Jehoash was  seven years old when he became king.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoash Repairs the Temple'
      title: Jehoash Repairs the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "In the seventh year of Jehu, Jehoash became king, and he reigned
        forty years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Zibiah of Beersheba. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jehoash did what  was right in the sight of the Lord all the days
        in which Jehoiada the priest instructed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: But the high places were not taken away; the people still sacrificed
        and burned incense on the high places.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Jehoash said to the priests, \u201CAll the money of the dedicated
        gifts that are brought into the house of the Lord\u2014each man\u2019s census
        money, each man\u2019s assessment money\u2014and all the money that a man
        purposes in his heart to bring into the house of the Lord, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "let the priests take it themselves, each from his constituency; and
        let them repair the damages of the temple, wherever any dilapidation is found.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now it was so, by the twenty-third year of King Jehoash, that the
        priests had not repaired the damages of the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So King Jehoash called Jehoiada the priest and the other priests,
        and said to them, \u201CWhy have you not repaired the damages of the temple?
        Now therefore, do not take more money from your constituency, but deliver
        it for repairing the damages of the temple.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And the priests agreed that they would neither receive more money
        from the people, nor repair the damages of the temple.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jehoiada the priest took a chest, bored a hole in its lid, and
        set it beside the altar, on the right side as one comes into the house of
        the Lord; and the priests who kept the door put there all the money brought
        into the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So it was, whenever they saw that there  was much money in the chest,
        that the king\u2019s scribe and the high priest came up and put it in bags,
        and counted the money that was found in the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they gave the money, which had been apportioned, into the hands
        of those who did the work, who had the oversight of the house of the Lord;
        and they paid it out to the carpenters and builders who worked on the house
        of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and to masons and stonecutters, and for buying timber and hewn stone,
        to repair the damage of the house of the Lord, and for all that was paid
        out to repair the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'However there were not made for the house of the Lord basins of silver,
        trimmers, sprinkling-bowls, trumpets, any articles of gold or articles of
        silver, from the money brought into the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But they gave that to the workmen, and they repaired the house of
        the Lord with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Moreover they did not require an account from the men into whose
        hand they delivered the money to be paid to workmen, for they dealt faithfully. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Hazael Threatens Jerusalem'
      title: Hazael Threatens Jerusalem
      number: 16
      content: The money from the trespass offerings and the money from the sin offerings
        was not brought into the house of the Lord. It belonged to the priests.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Hazael king of Syria went up and fought against Gath, and took it;
        then Hazael set his face to go up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Death of Joash'
      title: Death of Joash
      number: 18
      content: "And Jehoash king of Judah took all the sacred things that his fathers,
        Jehoshaphat and Jehoram and Ahaziah, kings of Judah, had dedicated, and his
        own sacred things, and all the gold found in the treasuries of the house
        of the Lord and in the king\u2019s house, and sent them to Hazael king of
        Syria. Then he went away from Jerusalem."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Joash, and all that he did, are they not
        written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And his servants arose and formed a conspiracy, and killed Joash
        in the house of the Millo, which goes down to Silla. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For Jozachar the son of Shimeath and Jehozabad the son of Shomer,
        his servants, struck him. So he died, and they buried him with his fathers
        in the City of David. Then Amaziah his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoahaz Reigns in Israel'
      title: Jehoahaz Reigns in Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'In the twenty-third year of Joash the son of Ahaziah, king of Judah,
        Jehoahaz the son of Jehu became king over Israel in Samaria, and  reigned
        seventeen years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, and followed the sins of
        Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. He did not depart from
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the anger of the Lord was aroused against Israel, and He delivered
        them into the hand of Hazael king of Syria, and into the hand of Ben-Hadad
        the son of Hazael, all their days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Jehoahaz pleaded with the Lord, and the Lord listened to him;
        for He saw the oppression of Israel, because the king of Syria oppressed
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the Lord gave Israel a deliverer, so that they escaped from
        under the hand of the Syrians; and the children of Israel dwelt in their
        tents as before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nevertheless they did not depart from the sins of the house of Jeroboam,
        who had made Israel sin, but walked in them; and the wooden image also remained
        in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For He left of the army of Jehoahaz only fifty horsemen, ten chariots,
        and ten thousand foot soldiers; for the king of Syria had destroyed them
        and made them like the dust at threshing.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoahaz, all that he did, and his might,
        are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Jehoash Reigns in Israel'
      title: Jehoash Reigns in Israel
      number: 9
      content: So Jehoahaz rested with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria.
        Then Joash his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In the thirty-seventh year of Joash king of Judah, Jehoash the son
        of Jehoahaz became king over Israel in Samaria, and  reigned sixteen years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And he did evil in the sight of the Lord. He did not depart from all
        the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin, but walked in
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Joash, all that he did, and his might
        with which he fought against Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written
        in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Death of Elisha'
      title: Death of Elisha
      number: 13
      content: So Joash rested with his fathers. Then Jeroboam sat on his throne.
        And Joash was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Elisha had become sick with the illness of which he would die. Then
        Joash the king of Israel came down to him, and wept over his face, and said,
        \u201CO my father, my father, the chariots of Israel and their horsemen!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Elisha said to him, \u201CTake a bow and some arrows.\u201D So
        he took himself a bow and some arrows. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said to the king of Israel, \u201CPut your hand on the bow.\u201D
        So he put his hand on  it, and Elisha put his hands on the king\u2019s hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201COpen the east window\u201D; and he opened it.
        Then Elisha said, \u201CShoot\u201D; and he shot. And he said, \u201CThe
        arrow of the Lord\u2019s deliverance and the arrow of deliverance from Syria;
        for you must strike the Syrians at Aphek till you have destroyed them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he said, \u201CTake the arrows\u201D; so he took them. And he
        said to the king of Israel, \u201CStrike the ground\u201D; so he struck three
        times, and stopped. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the man of God was angry with him, and said, \u201CYou should
        have struck five or six times; then you would have struck Syria till you
        had destroyed it!  But now you will strike Syria only three times.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Elisha died, and they buried him. And the raiding bands from
        Moab invaded the land in the spring of the year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Israel Recaptures Cities from Syria'
      title: Israel Recaptures Cities from Syria
      number: 21
      content: So it was, as they were burying a man, that suddenly they spied a
        band of  raiders; and they put the man in the tomb of Elisha; and when the
        man was let down and touched the bones of Elisha, he revived and stood on
        his feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Hazael king of Syria oppressed Israel all the days of Jehoahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: But the Lord was gracious to them, had compassion on them, and regarded
        them, because of His covenant with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and would not
        yet destroy them or cast them from His presence.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now Hazael king of Syria died. Then Ben-Hadad his son reigned in
        his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz recaptured from the hand of Ben-Hadad,
        the son of Hazael, the cities which he had taken out of the hand of Jehoahaz
        his father by war. Three times Joash defeated him and recaptured the cities
        of Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amaziah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Amaziah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'In the second year of Joash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel,
        Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jehoaddan of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord, yet not like
        his father David; he did everything as his father Joash had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: However the high places were not taken away, and the people still
        sacrificed and burned incense on the high places.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now it happened, as soon as the kingdom was established in his hand,
        that he executed his servants who had murdered his father the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But the children of the murderers he did not execute, according to
        what is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, in which the Lord commanded,
        saying, \u201CFathers shall not be put to death for their children, nor shall
        children be put to death for their fathers; but a person shall be put to
        death for his own sin.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He killed ten thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt, and took Sela
        by war, and called its name Joktheel to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Amaziah sent messengers to Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz, the
        son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, \u201CCome, let us face one another
        in  battle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Jehoash king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying,
        \u201CThe thistle that was in Lebanon sent to the cedar that was in Lebanon,
        saying, \u2018Give your daughter to my son as wife\u2019; and a wild beast
        that was in Lebanon passed by and trampled the thistle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You have indeed defeated Edom, and your heart has lifted you up.
        Glory in  that, and stay at home; for why should you meddle with trouble
        so that you fall\u2014you and Judah with you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Amaziah would not heed. Therefore Jehoash king of Israel went
        out; so he and Amaziah king of Judah faced one another at Beth Shemesh, which
        belongs to Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Judah was defeated by Israel, and every man fled to his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son
        of Jehoash, the son of Ahaziah, at Beth Shemesh; and he went to Jerusalem,
        and broke down the wall of Jerusalem from the Gate of Ephraim to the Corner
        Gate\u2014four hundred cubits. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he took all the gold and silver, all the articles that were found
        in the house of the Lord and in the treasuries of the king\u2019s house,
        and hostages, and returned to Samaria."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now the rest of the acts of Jehoash which he did\u2014his might,
        and how he fought with Amaziah king of Judah\u2014are they not written in
        the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So Jehoash rested with his fathers, and was buried in Samaria with
        the kings of Israel. Then Jeroboam his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, lived fifteen years after
        the death of Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, are they not written in the
        book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And they formed a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem, and he fled
        to Lachish; but they sent after him to Lachish and killed him there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Then they brought him on horses, and he was buried at Jerusalem with
        his fathers in the City of David.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And all the people of Judah took Azariah, who was sixteen years old,
        and made him king instead of his father Amaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Jeroboam II Reigns in Israel'
      title: Jeroboam II Reigns in Israel
      number: 22
      content: He built Elath and restored it to Judah, after the king rested with
        his fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the fifteenth year of Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah,
        Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel, became king in Samaria, and  reigned
        forty-one years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not depart from
        all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He restored the territory of Israel from the entrance of Hamath to
        the Sea of the Arabah, according to the word of the Lord God of Israel, which
        He had spoken through His servant Jonah the son of Amittai, the prophet who
        was from Gath Hepher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For the Lord  saw that the affliction of Israel was very bitter;
        and whether bond or free, there was no helper for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And the Lord did not say that He would blot out the name of Israel
        from under heaven; but He saved them by the hand of Jeroboam the son of Joash.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam, and all that he did\u2014his
        might, how he made war, and how he recaptured for Israel, from Damascus and
        Hamath, what  had  belonged to Judah\u2014are they not written in the book
        of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: So Jeroboam rested with his fathers, the kings of Israel. Then Zechariah
        his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Azariah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Azariah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'In the twenty-seventh year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Azariah the
        son of Amaziah, king of Judah, became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-two
        years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jecholiah of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord, according to
        all that his father Amaziah had done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'except that the high places were not removed; the people still sacrificed
        and burned incense on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Lord  struck the king, so that he was a leper until the
        day of his death; so he dwelt in an isolated house. And Jotham the king\u2019s
        son was over the royal house, judging the people of the land."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Azariah, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Zechariah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Zechariah Reigns in Israel
      number: 7
      content: So Azariah rested with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers
        in the City of David. Then Jotham his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the thirty-eighth year of Azariah king of Judah, Zechariah the
        son of Jeroboam reigned over Israel in Samaria six months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, as his fathers had done;
        he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made
        Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then Shallum the son of Jabesh conspired against him, and struck and
        killed him in front of the people; and he reigned in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Zechariah, indeed they are written in
        the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Shallum Reigns in Israel'
      title: Shallum Reigns in Israel
      number: 12
      content: "This was the word of the Lord which He spoke to Jehu, saying, \u201CYour
        sons shall sit on the throne of Israel to the fourth generation.\u201D And
        so it was."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Shallum the son of Jabesh became king in the thirty-ninth year of
        Uzziah king of Judah; and he reigned a full month in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For Menahem the son of Gadi went up from Tirzah, came to Samaria,
        and struck Shallum the son of Jabesh in Samaria and killed him; and he reigned
        in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Shallum, and the conspiracy which he
        led, indeed they are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Menahem Reigns in Israel'
      title: Menahem Reigns in Israel
      number: 16
      content: Then from Tirzah, Menahem attacked Tiphsah, all who were there, and
        its territory. Because they did not surrender, therefore he attacked it.
        All the women there who were with child he ripped open.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the thirty-ninth year of Azariah king of Judah, Menahem the son
        of Gadi became king over Israel, and  reigned ten years in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not depart all his
        days from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pul king of Assyria came against the land; and Menahem gave Pul a
        thousand talents of silver, that his hand might be with him to strengthen
        the kingdom under his control. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And Menahem exacted the money from Israel, from all the very wealthy,
        from each man fifty shekels of silver, to give to the king of Assyria. So
        the king of Assyria turned back, and did not stay there in the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Menahem, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Pekahiah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Pekahiah Reigns in Israel
      number: 22
      content: So Menahem rested with his fathers. Then Pekahiah his son reigned
        in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekahiah the son of
        Menahem became king over Israel in Samaria, and  reigned two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not depart from
        the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Pekah the son of Remaliah, an officer of his, conspired against
        him and killed him in Samaria, in the citadel of the king\u2019s house, along
        with Argob and Arieh; and with him were fifty men of Gilead. He killed him
        and reigned in his place."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Pekah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Pekah Reigns in Israel
      number: 26
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Pekahiah, and all that he did, indeed
        they are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'In the fifty-second year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekah the son
        of Remaliah became king over Israel in Samaria, and  reigned twenty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not depart from
        the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In the days of Pekah king of Israel, Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria
        came and took Ijon, Abel Beth Maachah, Janoah, Kedesh, Hazor, Gilead, and
        Galilee, all the land of Naphtali; and he carried them captive to Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then Hoshea the son of Elah led a conspiracy against Pekah the son
        of Remaliah, and struck and killed him; so he reigned in his place in the
        twentieth year of Jotham the son of Uzziah.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Jotham Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jotham Reigns in Judah
      number: 31
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Pekah, and all that he did, indeed they
        are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In the second year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of Israel,
        Jotham the son of Uzziah, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jerusha the daughter
        of Zadok. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord; he did according
        to all that his father Uzziah had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: However the high places were not removed; the people still sacrificed
        and burned incense on the high places. He built the Upper Gate of the house
        of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'In those days the Lord began to send Rezin king of Syria and Pekah
        the son of Remaliah against Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: So Jotham rested with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers
        in the City of David his father. Then Ahaz his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaz Reigns in Judah'
      title: Ahaz Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'In the seventeenth year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, Ahaz the son
        of Jotham, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Ahaz was twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen
        years in Jerusalem; and he did not do what  was right in the sight of the
        Lord his God, as his father David had  done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But he walked in the way of the kings of Israel; indeed he made his
        son pass through the fire, according to the abominations of the nations whom
        the Lord had cast out from before the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And he sacrificed and burned incense on the high places, on the hills,
        and under every green tree.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Rezin king of Syria and Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of Israel,
        came up to Jerusalem to make war; and they besieged Ahaz but could not overcome
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: At that time Rezin king of Syria captured Elath for Syria, and drove
        the men of Judah from Elath. Then the Edomites went to Elath, and dwell there
        to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Ahaz sent messengers to Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria, saying,
        \u201CI am your servant and your son. Come up and save me from the hand of
        the king of Syria and from the hand of the king of Israel, who rise up against
        me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Ahaz took the silver and gold that was found in the house of
        the Lord, and in the treasuries of the king\u2019s house, and sent it  as
        a present to the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So the king of Assyria heeded him; for the king of Assyria went up
        against Damascus and took it, carried its  people captive to Kir, and killed
        Rezin.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now King Ahaz went to Damascus to meet Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria,
        and saw an altar that was at Damascus; and King Ahaz sent to Urijah the priest
        the design of the altar and its pattern, according to all its workmanship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Urijah the priest built an altar according to all that King
        Ahaz had sent from Damascus. So Urijah the priest made it before King Ahaz
        came back from Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when the king came back from Damascus, the king saw the altar;
        and the king approached the altar and made offerings on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So he burned his burnt offering and his grain offering; and he poured
        his drink offering and sprinkled the blood of his peace offerings on the
        altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He also brought the bronze altar which was before the Lord, from
        the front of the temple\u2014from between the new altar and the house of
        the Lord\u2014and put it on the north side of the new altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then King Ahaz commanded Urijah the priest, saying, \u201COn the
        great new altar burn the morning burnt offering, the evening grain offering,
        the king\u2019s burnt sacrifice, and his grain offering, with the burnt offering
        of all the people of the land, their grain offering, and their drink offerings;
        and sprinkle on it all the blood of the burnt offering and all the blood
        of the sacrifice. And the bronze altar shall be for me to inquire by.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Thus did Urijah the priest, according to all that King Ahaz commanded.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And King Ahaz cut off the panels of the carts, and removed the lavers
        from them; and he took down the Sea from the bronze oxen that were under
        it, and put it on a pavement of stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Also he removed the Sabbath pavilion which they had built in the
        temple, and he removed the king\u2019s outer entrance from the house of the
        Lord, on account of the king of Assyria."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Ahaz which he did, are they not written
        in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So Ahaz rested with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in
        the City of David. Then Hezekiah his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hoshea Reigns in Israel'
      title: Hoshea Reigns in Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'In the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah, Hoshea the son of Elah
        became king of Israel in Samaria, and  he  reigned nine years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, but not as the kings of
        Israel who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shalmaneser king of Assyria came up against him; and Hoshea became
        his vassal, and paid him tribute money. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Israel Carried Captive to Assyria'
      title: Israel Carried Captive to Assyria
      number: 4
      content: And the king of Assyria uncovered a conspiracy by Hoshea; for he had
        sent messengers to So, king of Egypt, and brought no tribute to the king
        of Assyria, as he  had  done year by year. Therefore the king of Assyria
        shut him up, and bound him in prison.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the king of Assyria went throughout all the land, and went up
        to Samaria and besieged it for three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: In the ninth year of Hoshea, the king of Assyria took Samaria and
        carried Israel away to Assyria, and placed them in Halah and by the Habor,
        the River of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For so it was that the children of Israel had sinned against the
        Lord their God, who had brought them up out of the land of Egypt, from under
        the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt; and they had feared other gods, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and had walked in the statutes of the nations whom the Lord had cast
        out from before the children of Israel, and of the kings of Israel, which
        they had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Also the children of Israel secretly did against the Lord their God
        things that were not right, and they built for themselves high places in
        all their cities, from watchtower to fortified city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They set up for themselves sacred pillars and wooden images on every
        high hill and under every green tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'There they burned incense on all the high places, like the nations
        whom the Lord had carried away before them; and they did wicked things to
        provoke the Lord to anger, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "for they served idols, of which the Lord had said to them, \u201CYou
        shall not do this thing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet the Lord testified against Israel and against Judah, by all of
        His prophets, every seer, saying, \u201CTurn from your evil ways, and keep
        My commandments and My statutes, according to all the law which I commanded
        your fathers, and which I sent to you by My servants the prophets.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Nevertheless they would not hear, but stiffened their necks, like
        the necks of their fathers, who did not believe in the Lord their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they rejected His statutes and His covenant that He had made
        with their fathers, and His testimonies which He had testified against them;
        they followed idols, became idolaters, and went after the nations who were
        all around them, concerning whom the Lord had charged them that they should
        not do like them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So they left all the commandments of the Lord their God, made for
        themselves a molded image and two calves, made a wooden image and worshiped
        all the host of heaven, and served Baal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they caused their sons and daughters to pass through the fire,
        practiced witchcraft and soothsaying, and sold themselves to do evil in the
        sight of the Lord, to provoke Him to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Therefore the Lord was very angry with Israel, and removed them from
        His sight; there was none left but the tribe of Judah alone.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Also Judah did not keep the commandments of the Lord their God, but
        walked in the statutes of Israel which they made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the Lord rejected all the descendants of Israel, afflicted them,
        and delivered them into the hand of plunderers, until He had cast them from
        His sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For He tore Israel from the house of David, and they made Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat king. Then Jeroboam drove Israel from following the Lord,
        and made them commit a great sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the children of Israel walked in all the sins of Jeroboam which
        he did; they did not depart from them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Assyria Resettles Samaria'
      title: Assyria Resettles Samaria
      number: 23
      content: until the Lord removed Israel out of His sight, as He had said by
        all His servants the prophets. So Israel was carried away from their own
        land to Assyria, as  it  is to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the king of Assyria brought people from Babylon, Cuthah, Ava,
        Hamath, and from Sepharvaim, and placed them in the cities of Samaria instead
        of the children of Israel; and they took possession of Samaria and dwelt
        in its cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And it was so, at the beginning of their dwelling there, that they
        did not fear the Lord; therefore the Lord sent lions among them, which killed
        some of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So they spoke to the king of Assyria, saying, \u201CThe nations whom
        you have removed and placed in the cities of Samaria do not know the rituals
        of the God of the land; therefore He has sent lions among them, and indeed,
        they are killing them because they do not know the rituals of the God of
        the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king of Assyria commanded, saying, \u201CSend there one
        of the priests whom you brought from there; let him go and dwell there, and
        let him teach them the rituals of the God of the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Then one of the priests whom they had carried away from Samaria came
        and dwelt in Bethel, and taught them how they should fear the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'However every nation continued to make gods of its own, and put them 
        in the shrines on the high places which the Samaritans had made, every nation
        in the cities where they dwelt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The men of Babylon made Succoth Benoth, the men of Cuth made Nergal,
        the men of Hamath made Ashima, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and the Avites made Nibhaz and Tartak; and the Sepharvites burned
        their children in fire to Adrammelech and Anammelech, the gods of Sepharvaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So they feared the Lord, and from every class they appointed for
        themselves priests of the high places, who sacrificed for them in the shrines
        of the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "They feared the Lord, yet served their own gods\u2014according to
        the rituals of the nations from among whom they were carried away."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'To this day they continue practicing the former rituals; they do
        not fear the Lord, nor do they follow their statutes or their ordinances,
        or the law and commandment which the Lord had commanded the children of Jacob,
        whom He named Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "with whom the Lord had made a covenant and charged them, saying:
        \u201CYou shall not fear other gods, nor bow down to them nor serve them
        nor sacrifice to them; "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'but the Lord, who brought you up from the land of Egypt with great
        power and an outstretched arm, Him you shall fear, Him you shall worship,
        and to Him you shall offer sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And the statutes, the ordinances, the law, and the commandment which
        He wrote for you, you shall be careful to observe forever; you shall not
        fear other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And the covenant that I have made with you, you shall not forget,
        nor shall you fear other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But the Lord your God you shall fear; and He will deliver you from
        the hand of all your enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'However they did not obey, but they followed their former rituals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So these nations feared the Lord, yet served their carved images;
        also their children and their children\u2019s children have continued doing
        as their fathers did, even to this day."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Hezekiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the third year of Hoshea the son of Elah,
        king of Israel, that  Hezekiah the son of Ahaz, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was  Abi the daughter
        of Zechariah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord, according to
        all that his father David had done.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He removed the high places and broke the sacred pillars, cut down
        the wooden image and broke in pieces the bronze serpent that Moses had made;
        for until those days the children of Israel burned incense to it, and called
        it Nehushtan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He trusted in the Lord God of Israel, so that after him was none
        like him among all the kings of Judah, nor who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For he held fast to the Lord; he did not depart from following Him,
        but kept His commandments, which the Lord had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord  was with him; he prospered wherever he went. And he rebelled
        against the king of Assyria and did not serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He subdued the Philistines, as far as Gaza and its territory, from
        watchtower to fortified city.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the fourth year of King Hezekiah, which was
        the seventh year of Hoshea the son of Elah, king of Israel, that Shalmaneser
        king of Assyria came up against Samaria and besieged it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And at the end of three years they took it. In the sixth year of
        Hezekiah, that is,  the ninth year of Hoshea king of Israel, Samaria was
        taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the king of Assyria carried Israel away captive to Assyria,
        and put them in Halah and by the Habor, the River of Gozan, and in the cities
        of the Medes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: because they did not obey the voice of the Lord their God, but transgressed
        His covenant and all that Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded; and
        they would neither hear nor do them.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And in the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of
        Assyria came up against all the fortified cities of Judah and took them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Hezekiah king of Judah sent to the king of Assyria at Lachish,
        saying, \u201CI have done wrong; turn away from me; whatever you impose on
        me I will pay.\u201D And the king of Assyria assessed Hezekiah king of Judah
        three hundred talents of silver and thirty talents of gold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So Hezekiah gave him all the silver that was found in the house of
        the Lord and in the treasuries of the king\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Sennacherib Boasts Against the Lord'
      title: Sennacherib Boasts Against the Lord
      number: 16
      content: At that time Hezekiah stripped the  gold  from the doors of the temple
        of the Lord, and from the pillars which Hezekiah king of Judah had overlaid,
        and gave it to the king of Assyria.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the king of Assyria sent the Tartan, the Rabsaris,  and the
        Rabshakeh from Lachish, with a great army against Jerusalem, to King Hezekiah.
        And they went up and came to Jerusalem. When they had come up, they went
        and stood by the aqueduct from the upper pool, which was on the highway to
        the Fuller\u2019s Field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when they had called to the king, Eliakim the son of Hilkiah,
        who was over the household, Shebna the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph,
        the recorder, came out to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CSay now to Hezekiah, \u2018Thus
        says the great king, the king of Assyria: \u201CWhat confidence is this in
        which you trust? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You speak of having plans and power for war; but they  are mere words.
        And in whom do you trust, that you rebel against me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now look! You are trusting in the staff of this broken reed, Egypt,
        on which if a man leans, it will go into his hand and pierce it. So is Pharaoh
        king of Egypt to all who trust in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But if you say to me, \u2018We trust in the Lord our God,\u2019 is
        it not He whose high places and whose altars Hezekiah has taken away, and
        said to Judah and Jerusalem, \u2018You shall worship before this altar in
        Jerusalem\u2019?\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now therefore, I urge you, give a pledge to my master the king of
        Assyria, and I will give you two thousand horses\u2014if you are able on
        your part to put riders on them! "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "How then will you repel one captain of the least of my master\u2019s
        servants, and put your trust in Egypt for chariots and horsemen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Have I now come up without the Lord against this place to destroy
        it? The Lord said to me, \u2018Go up against this land, and destroy it.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, Shebna, and Joah said to the Rabshakeh,
        \u201CPlease speak to your servants in Aramaic, for we understand it; and
        do not speak to us in Hebrew in the hearing of the people who are on the
        wall.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CHas my master sent me to your
        master and to you to speak these words, and not to the men who sit on the
        wall, who will eat and drink their own waste with you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh stood and called out with a loud voice in Hebrew,
        and spoke, saying, \u201CHear the word of the great king, the king of Assyria! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Thus says the king: \u2018Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he
        shall not be able to deliver you from his hand; "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "nor let Hezekiah make you trust in the Lord, saying, \u201CThe Lord
        will surely deliver us; this city shall not be given into the hand of the
        king of Assyria.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Do not listen to Hezekiah; for thus says the king of Assyria: \u2018Make
        peace with me by a present and come out to me; and every one of you eat from
        his own vine and every one from his own fig tree, and every one of you drink
        the waters of his own cistern; "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land
        of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards, a land of olive groves
        and honey, that you may live and not die. But do not listen to Hezekiah,
        lest he persuade you, saying, \u201CThe Lord will deliver us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Has any of the gods of the nations at all delivered its land from
        the hand of the king of Assyria? '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim
        and Hena and Ivah? Indeed, have they delivered Samaria from my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Who among all the gods of the lands have delivered their countries
        from my hand, that the Lord should deliver Jerusalem from my hand?\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "But the people held their peace and answered him not a word; for
        the king\u2019s commandment was, \u201CDo not answer him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, Shebna
        the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came to Hezekiah with
        their clothes torn, and told him the words of the Rabshakeh.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaiah Assures Deliverance'
      title: Isaiah Assures Deliverance
      number: 1
      content: 'And so it was, when King Hezekiah heard it, that he tore his clothes,
        covered himself with sackcloth, and went into the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then he sent Eliakim, who was over the household, Shebna the scribe,
        and the elders of the priests, covered with sackcloth, to Isaiah the prophet,
        the son of Amoz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CThus says Hezekiah: \u2018This day is
        a day of trouble, and rebuke, and blasphemy; for the children have come to
        birth, but there  is no strength to bring them forth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It may be that the Lord your God will hear all the words of the Rabshakeh,
        whom his master the king of Assyria has sent to reproach the living God,
        and will rebuke the words which the Lord your God has heard. Therefore lift
        up your prayer for the remnant that is left.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Isaiah said to them, \u201CThus you shall say to your master,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CDo not be afraid of the words which you have
        heard, with which the servants of the king of Assyria have blasphemed Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Sennacherib\u2019s Threat and Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Sennacherib\u2019s Threat and Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 7
      content: "Surely I will send a spirit upon him, and he shall hear a rumor and
        return to his own land; and I will cause him to fall by the sword in his
        own land.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the Rabshakeh returned and found the king of Assyria warring
        against Libnah, for he heard that he had departed from Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the king heard concerning Tirhakah king of Ethiopia, \u201CLook,
        he has come out to make war with you.\u201D So he again sent messengers to
        Hezekiah, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus you shall speak to Hezekiah king of Judah, saying: \u2018Do
        not let your God in whom you trust deceive you, saying, \u201CJerusalem shall
        not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Look! You have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all lands
        by utterly destroying them; and shall you be delivered? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Have the gods of the nations delivered those whom my fathers have
        destroyed, Gozan and Haran and Rezeph, and the people of Eden who were in
        Telassar? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, and the king of the
        city of Sepharvaim, Hena, and Ivah?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Hezekiah received the letter from the hand of the messengers,
        and read it; and Hezekiah went up to the house of the Lord, and spread it
        before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Hezekiah prayed before the Lord, and said: \u201CO Lord God
        of Israel, the  One  who dwells between the cherubim, You are God, You alone,
        of all the kingdoms of the earth. You have made heaven and earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Incline Your ear, O Lord, and hear; open Your eyes, O Lord, and see;
        and hear the words of Sennacherib, which he has sent to reproach the living
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Truly, Lord, the kings of Assyria have laid waste the nations and
        their lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and have cast their gods into the fire; for they were  not gods,
        but the work of men\u2019s hands\u2014wood and stone. Therefore they destroyed
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Word of the Lord Concerning Sennacherib'
      title: The Word of the Lord Concerning Sennacherib
      number: 19
      content: "Now therefore, O Lord our God, I pray, save us from his hand, that
        all the kingdoms of the earth may know that You are the Lord God, You alone.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, \u201CThus
        says the Lord God of Israel: \u2018Because you have prayed to Me against
        Sennacherib king of Assyria, I have heard.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "This is the word which the Lord has spoken concerning him:\u2018The
        virgin, the daughter of Zion,Has despised you, laughed you to scorn;The daughter
        of JerusalemHas shaken her head behind your back!"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018Whom have you reproached and blasphemed?Against whom have you
        raised your voice,And lifted up your eyes on high?Against the Holy One of
        Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "By your messengers you have reproached the Lord,And said: \u201CBy
        the multitude of my chariotsI have come up to the height of the mountains,To
        the limits of Lebanon;I will cut down its tall cedarsAnd its choice cypress
        trees;I will enter the extremity of its borders,To its fruitful forest."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I have dug and drunk strange water,And with the soles of my feet
        I have dried upAll the brooks of defense.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u2018Did you not hear long agoHow  I made it,From ancient times
        that I formed it?Now I have brought it to pass,That you should beFor crushing
        fortified cities into heaps of ruins."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Therefore their inhabitants had little power;They were dismayed and
        confounded;They were as the grass of the fieldAnd the green herb,As  the
        grass on the housetopsAnd grain blighted before it is grown.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u2018But I know your dwelling place,Your going out and your coming
        in,And your rage against Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Because your rage against Me and your tumultHave come up to My ears,Therefore
        I will put My hook in your noseAnd My bridle in your lips,And I will turn
        you backBy the way which you came.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u2018This shall  be a sign to you:You shall eat this year such as
        grows of itself,And in the second year what springs from the same;Also in
        the third year sow and reap,Plant vineyards and eat the fruit of them."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And the remnant who have escaped of the house of JudahShall again
        take root downward,And bear fruit upward.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For out of Jerusalem shall go a remnant,And those who escape from
        Mount Zion.The zeal of the Lord of hosts will do this.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord concerning the king of Assyria:\u2018He
        shall not come into this city,Nor shoot an arrow there,Nor come before it
        with shield,Nor build a siege mound against it."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "By the way that he came,By the same shall he return;And he shall
        not come into this city,\u2019Says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: "34: Sennacherib\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      title: "Sennacherib\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      number: 34
      content: "\u2018For I will defend this city, to save itFor My own sake and
        for My servant David\u2019s sake.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And it came to pass on a certain night that the angel of the Lord
        went out, and killed in the camp of the Assyrians one hundred and eighty-five
        thousand; and when people arose early in the morning, there were the corpses\u2014all
        dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So Sennacherib king of Assyria departed and went away, returned home,
        and remained at Nineveh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Now it came to pass, as he was worshiping in the temple of Nisroch
        his god, that his sons Adrammelech and Sharezer struck him down with the
        sword; and they escaped into the land of Ararat. Then Esarhaddon his son
        reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hezekiah\u2019s Life Extended"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Life Extended"
      number: 1
      content: "In those days Hezekiah was sick and near death. And Isaiah the prophet,
        the son of Amoz, went to him and said to him, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Set
        your house in order, for you shall die, and not live.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then he turned his face toward the wall, and prayed to the Lord,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CRemember now, O Lord, I pray, how I have walked before You
        in truth and with a loyal heart, and have done what  was good in Your sight.\u201D
        And Hezekiah wept bitterly."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And it happened, before Isaiah had gone out into the middle court,
        that the word of the Lord came to him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CReturn and tell Hezekiah the leader of My people, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord, the God of David your father: \u201CI have heard your prayer,
        I have seen your tears; surely I will heal you. On the third day you shall
        go up to the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And I will add to your days fifteen years. I will deliver you and
        this city from the hand of the king of Assyria; and I will defend this city
        for My own sake, and for the sake of My servant David.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Isaiah said, \u201CTake a lump of figs.\u201D So they took and
        laid it on the boil, and he recovered."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CWhat is the sign that the Lord
        will heal me, and that I shall go up to the house of the Lord the third day?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Isaiah said, \u201CThis is the sign to you from the Lord, that
        the Lord will do the thing which He has spoken: shall the shadow go forward
        ten degrees or go backward ten degrees?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Hezekiah answered, \u201CIt is an easy thing for the shadow to
        go down ten degrees; no, but let the shadow go backward ten degrees.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Babylonian Envoys'
      title: The Babylonian Envoys
      number: 11
      content: So Isaiah the prophet cried out to the Lord, and He brought the shadow
        ten degrees backward, by which it had gone down on the sundial of Ahaz.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'At that time Berodach-Baladan the son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he heard that Hezekiah had been
        sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Hezekiah was attentive to them, and showed them all the house
        of his treasures\u2014the silver and gold, the spices and precious ointment,
        and all his armory\u2014all that was found among his treasures. There was
        nothing in his house or in all his dominion that Hezekiah did not show them."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet went to King Hezekiah, and said to him, \u201CWhat
        did these men say, and from where did they come to you?\u201DSo Hezekiah
        said, \u201CThey came from a far country, from Babylon.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat have they seen in your house?\u201DSo Hezekiah
        answered, \u201CThey have seen all that is in my house; there is nothing
        among my treasures that I have not shown them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHear the word of the Lord: "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Behold, the days are coming when all that is in your house,
        and what your fathers have accumulated until this day, shall be carried to
        Babylon; nothing shall be left,\u2019 says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018And they shall take away some of your sons who will descend
        from you, whom you will beget; and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of
        the king of Babylon.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Death of Hezekiah'
      title: Death of Hezekiah
      number: 19
      content: "So Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CThe word of the Lord which you
        have spoken is good!\u201D For he said, \u201CWill there not be peace and
        truth at least in my days?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah\u2014all his might, and how
        he made a pool and a tunnel and brought water into the city\u2014are they
        not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: So Hezekiah rested with his fathers. Then Manasseh his son reigned
        in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Manasseh Reigns in Judah'
      title: Manasseh Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned
        fifty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hephzibah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to the abominations
        of the nations whom the Lord had cast out before the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For he rebuilt the high places which Hezekiah his father had destroyed;
        he raised up altars for Baal, and made a wooden image, as Ahab king of Israel
        had done; and he worshiped all the host of heaven and served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He also built altars in the house of the Lord, of which the Lord
        had said, \u201CIn Jerusalem I will put My name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts
        of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Also he made his son pass through the fire, practiced soothsaying,
        used witchcraft, and consulted spiritists and mediums. He did much evil in
        the sight of the Lord, to provoke Him to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He even set a carved image of Asherah that he had made, in the house
        of which the Lord had said to David and to Solomon his son, \u201CIn this
        house and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel,
        I will put My name forever; "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and I will not make the feet of Israel wander anymore from the land
        which I gave their fathers\u2014only if they are careful to do according
        to all that I have commanded them, and according to all the law that My servant
        Moses commanded them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: But they paid no attention, and Manasseh seduced them to do more evil
        than the nations whom the Lord had destroyed before the children of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the Lord spoke by His servants the prophets, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBecause Manasseh king of Judah has done these abominations
        (he has acted more wickedly than all the Amorites who were before him, and
        has also made Judah sin with his idols), "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord God of Israel: \u2018Behold, I am bringing
        such calamity upon Jerusalem and Judah, that whoever hears of it, both his
        ears will tingle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I will stretch over Jerusalem the measuring line of Samaria and
        the plummet of the house of Ahab; I will wipe Jerusalem as one wipes a dish,
        wiping it and turning it upside down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So I will forsake the remnant of My inheritance and deliver them
        into the hand of their enemies; and they shall become victims of plunder
        to all their enemies, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "because they have done evil in My sight, and have provoked Me to
        anger since the day their fathers came out of Egypt, even to this day.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Moreover Manasseh shed very much innocent blood, till he had filled
        Jerusalem from one end to another, besides his sin by which he made Judah
        sin, in doing evil in the sight of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh\u2014all that he did, and the
        sin that he committed\u2014are they not written in the book of the chronicles
        of the kings of Judah? "
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Amon\u2019s Reign and Death"
      title: "Amon\u2019s Reign and Death"
      number: 18
      content: So Manasseh rested with his fathers, and was buried in the garden
        of his own house, in the garden of Uzza. Then his son Amon reigned in his
        place.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        two years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Meshullemeth the daughter
        of Haruz of Jotbah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, as his father Manasseh
        had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So he walked in all the ways that his father had walked; and he served
        the idols that his father had served, and worshiped them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He forsook the Lord God of his fathers, and did not walk in the way
        of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the servants of Amon conspired against him, and killed the king
        in his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: But the people of the land executed all those who had conspired against
        King Amon. Then the people of the land made his son Josiah king in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Amon which he did, are they not written
        in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And he was buried in his tomb in the garden of Uzza. Then Josiah his
        son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Josiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "Josiah was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned thirty-one
        years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jedidah the daughter of Adaiah
        of Bozkath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Hilkiah Finds the Book of the Law'
      title: Hilkiah Finds the Book of the Law
      number: 2
      content: And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord, and walked in
        all the ways of his father David; he did not turn aside to the right hand
        or to the left.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now it came to pass, in the eighteenth year of King Josiah, that
        the king sent Shaphan the scribe, the son of Azaliah, the son of Meshullam,
        to the house of the Lord, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGo up to Hilkiah the high priest, that he may count the money
        which has been brought into the house of the Lord, which the doorkeepers
        have gathered from the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And let them deliver it into the hand of those doing the work, who
        are the overseers in the house of the Lord; let them give it to those who
        are in the house of the Lord doing the work, to repair the damages of the
        house\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "to carpenters and builders and masons\u2014and to buy timber and
        hewn stone to repair the house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "However there need be no accounting made with them of the money delivered
        into their hand, because they deal faithfully.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Hilkiah the high priest said to Shaphan the scribe, \u201CI
        have found the Book of the Law in the house of the Lord.\u201D And Hilkiah
        gave the book to Shaphan, and he read it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Shaphan the scribe went to the king, bringing the king word, saying,
        \u201CYour servants have gathered the money that was found in the house,
        and have delivered it into the hand of those who do the work, who oversee
        the house of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Shaphan the scribe showed the king, saying, \u201CHilkiah the
        priest has given me a book.\u201D And Shaphan read it before the king."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now it happened, when the king heard the words of the Book of the
        Law, that he tore his clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the king commanded Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam the son of Shaphan,
        Achbor the son of Michaiah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah a servant of the
        king, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo, inquire of the Lord for me, for the people and for all
        Judah, concerning the words of this book that has been found; for great is 
        the wrath of the Lord that is aroused against us, because our fathers have
        not obeyed the words of this book, to do according to all that is written
        concerning us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam, Achbor, Shaphan, and Asaiah went to
        Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tikvah, the son of
        Harhas, keeper of the wardrobe. (She dwelt in Jerusalem in the Second Quarter.)
        And they spoke with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then she said to them, \u201CThus says the Lord God of Israel, \u2018Tell
        the man who sent you to Me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Behold, I will bring calamity on
        this place and on its inhabitants\u2014all the words of the book which the
        king of Judah has read\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "because they have forsaken Me and burned incense to other gods, that
        they might provoke Me to anger with all the works of their hands. Therefore
        My wrath shall be aroused against this place and shall not be quenched.\u2019
        \u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But as for the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire of the Lord,
        in this manner you shall speak to him, \u2018Thus says the Lord God of Israel:
        \u201CConcerning the words which you have heard\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "because your heart was tender, and you humbled yourself before the
        Lord when you heard what I spoke against this place and against its inhabitants,
        that they would become a desolation and a curse, and you tore your clothes
        and wept before Me, I also have heard you,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CSurely, therefore, I will gather you to your fathers, and you
        shall be gathered to your grave in peace; and your eyes shall not see all
        the calamity which I will bring on this place.\u201D \u2019 \u201D So they
        brought back word to the king."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah Restores True Worship'
      title: Josiah Restores True Worship
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the king sent them to gather all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The king went up to the house of the Lord with all the men of Judah,
        and with him all the inhabitants of Jerusalem\u2014the priests and the prophets
        and all the people, both small and great. And he read in their hearing all
        the words of the Book of the Covenant which had been found in the house of
        the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the king stood by a pillar and made a covenant before the Lord,
        to follow the Lord and to keep His commandments and His testimonies and His
        statutes, with all his heart and all his soul, to perform the words of this
        covenant that were written in this book. And all the people took a stand
        for the covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the king commanded Hilkiah the high priest, the priests of the
        second order, and the doorkeepers, to bring out of the temple of the Lord
        all the articles that were made for Baal, for Asherah, and for all the host
        of heaven; and he burned them outside Jerusalem in the fields of Kidron,
        and carried their ashes to Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then he removed the idolatrous priests whom the kings of Judah had
        ordained to burn incense on the high places in the cities of Judah and in
        the places all around Jerusalem, and those who burned incense to Baal, to
        the sun, to the moon, to the constellations, and to all the host of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he brought out the wooden image from the house of the Lord, to
        the Brook Kidron outside Jerusalem, burned it at the Brook Kidron and ground
        it to ashes, and threw its ashes on the graves of the common people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then he tore down the ritual booths of the perverted persons that
        were in the house of the Lord, where the women wove hangings for the wooden
        image. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he brought all the priests from the cities of Judah, and defiled
        the high places where the priests had burned incense, from Geba to Beersheba;
        also he broke down the high places at the gates which were at the entrance
        of the Gate of Joshua the governor of the city, which were to the left of
        the city gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Nevertheless the priests of the high places did not come up to the
        altar of the Lord in Jerusalem, but they ate unleavened bread among their
        brethren.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he defiled Topheth, which is in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom,
        that no man might make his son or his daughter pass through the fire to Molech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then he removed the horses that the kings of Judah had dedicated
        to the sun, at the entrance to the house of the Lord, by the chamber of Nathan-Melech,
        the officer who was in the court; and he burned the chariots of the sun with
        fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The altars that were  on the roof, the upper chamber of Ahaz, which
        the kings of Judah had made, and the altars which Manasseh had made in the
        two courts of the house of the Lord, the king broke down and pulverized there,
        and threw their dust into the Brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the king defiled the high places that were east of Jerusalem,
        which were on the south of the Mount of Corruption, which Solomon king of
        Israel had built for Ashtoreth the abomination of the Sidonians, for Chemosh
        the abomination of the Moabites, and for Milcom the abomination of the people
        of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And he broke in pieces the sacred pillars and cut down the wooden
        images, and filled their places with the bones of men.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Moreover the altar that was at Bethel, and the high place which Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin, had made, both that altar and the
        high place he broke down; and he burned the high place and crushed it to
        powder, and burned the wooden image. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'As Josiah turned, he saw the tombs that were there on the mountain.
        And he sent and took the bones out of the tombs and burned them on the altar,
        and defiled it according to the word of the Lord which the man of God proclaimed,
        who proclaimed these words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhat gravestone is this that I see?\u201DSo the
        men of the city told him, \u201CIt  is  the tomb of the man of God who came
        from Judah and proclaimed these things which you have done against the altar
        of Bethel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said, \u201CLet him alone; let no one move his bones.\u201D
        So they let his bones alone, with the bones of the prophet who came from
        Samaria."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now Josiah also took away all the shrines of the high places that
        were  in the cities of Samaria, which the kings of Israel had made to provoke
        the Lord to anger; and he did to them according to all the deeds he had done
        in Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He executed all the priests of the high places who were there, on
        the altars, and burned men\u2019s bones on them; and he returned to Jerusalem."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the king commanded all the people, saying, \u201CKeep the Passover
        to the Lord your God, as it  is written in this Book of the Covenant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Such a Passover surely had never been held since the days of the
        judges who judged Israel, nor in all the days of the kings of Israel and
        the kings of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But in the eighteenth year of King Josiah this Passover was held
        before the Lord in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Moreover Josiah put away those who consulted mediums and spiritists,
        the household gods and idols, all the abominations that were seen in the
        land of Judah and in Jerusalem, that he might perform the words of the law
        which were written in the book that Hilkiah the priest found in the house
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Impending Judgment on Judah'
      title: Impending Judgment on Judah
      number: 25
      content: Now before him there was no king like him, who turned to the Lord
        with all his heart, with all his soul, and with all his might, according
        to all the Law of Moses; nor after him did any arise like him.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Nevertheless the Lord did not turn from the fierceness of His great
        wrath, with which His anger was aroused against Judah, because of all the
        provocations with which Manasseh had provoked Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Josiah Dies in Battle'
      title: Josiah Dies in Battle
      number: 27
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CI will also remove Judah from My sight,
        as I have removed Israel, and will cast off this city Jerusalem which I have
        chosen, and the house of which I said, \u2018My name shall be there.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Josiah, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In his days Pharaoh Necho king of Egypt went to the aid of the king
        of Assyria, to the River Euphrates; and King Josiah went against him. And
        Pharaoh  Necho killed him at Megiddo when he confronted him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoahaz'
      title: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoahaz
      number: 30
      content: "Then his servants moved his body in a chariot from Megiddo, brought
        him to Jerusalem, and buried him in his own tomb. And the people of the land
        took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah, anointed him, and made him king in his father\u2019s
        place."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned
        three months in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was  Hamutal the daughter
        of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his
        fathers had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now Pharaoh Necho put him in prison at Riblah in the land of Hamath,
        that he might not reign in Jerusalem; and he imposed on the land a tribute
        of one hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Jehoiakim Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoiakim Reigns in Judah
      number: 34
      content: Then Pharaoh Necho made Eliakim the son of Josiah king in place of
        his father Josiah, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. And Pharaoh took Jehoahaz
        and went to Egypt, and he died there.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So Jehoiakim gave the silver and gold to Pharaoh; but he taxed the
        land to give money according to the command of Pharaoh; he exacted the silver
        and gold from the people of the land, from every one according to his assessment,
        to give it to Pharaoh Necho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Zebudah the daughter
        of Pedaiah of Rumah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his
        fathers had done.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judah Overrun by Enemies'
      title: Judah Overrun by Enemies
      number: 1
      content: 'In his days Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up, and Jehoiakim
        became his vassal for three years. Then he turned and rebelled against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Lord sent against him raiding bands of Chaldeans, bands of
        Syrians, bands of Moabites, and bands of the people of Ammon; He sent them
        against Judah to destroy it, according to the word of the Lord which He had
        spoken by His servants the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Surely at the commandment of the Lord  this came upon Judah, to remove
        them from His sight because of the sins of Manasseh, according to all that
        he had done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: and also because of the innocent blood that he had shed; for he had
        filled Jerusalem with innocent blood, which the Lord would not pardon.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So Jehoiakim rested with his fathers. Then Jehoiachin his son reigned
        in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoiachin'
      title: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoiachin
      number: 7
      content: And the king of Egypt did not come out of his land anymore, for the
        king of Babylon had taken all that belonged to the king of Egypt from the
        Brook of Egypt to the River Euphrates.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jehoiachin was eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned
        in Jerusalem three months. His mother\u2019s name was Nehushta the daughter
        of Elnathan of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his
        father had done.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'At that time the servants of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came
        up against Jerusalem, and the city was besieged. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came against the city, as his
        servants were besieging it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Captivity of Jerusalem'
      title: The Captivity of Jerusalem
      number: 12
      content: Then Jehoiachin king of Judah, his mother, his servants, his princes,
        and his officers went out to the king of Babylon; and the king of Babylon,
        in the eighth year of his reign, took him prisoner.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he carried out from there all the treasures of the house of the
        Lord and the treasures of the king\u2019s house, and he cut in pieces all
        the articles of gold which Solomon king of Israel had made in the temple
        of the Lord, as the Lord had said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Also he carried into captivity all Jerusalem: all the captains and
        all the mighty men of valor, ten thousand captives, and all the craftsmen
        and smiths. None remained except the poorest people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he carried Jehoiachin captive to Babylon. The king\u2019s mother,
        the king\u2019s wives, his officers, and the mighty of the land he carried
        into captivity from Jerusalem to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Zedekiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Zedekiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 16
      content: All the valiant men, seven thousand, and craftsmen and smiths, one
        thousand, all who  were strong and fit for war, these the king of Babylon
        brought captive to Babylon.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the king of Babylon made Mattaniah, Jehoiachin\u2019s uncle,
        king in his place, and changed his name to Zedekiah."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was  Hamutal the daughter
        of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He also did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that
        Jehoiakim had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: For because of the anger of the Lord  this happened in Jerusalem and
        Judah, that He finally cast them out from His presence. Then Zedekiah rebelled
        against the king of Babylon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall and Captivity of Judah'
      title: The Fall and Captivity of Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth
        month, on the tenth day of the month, that Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon
        and all his army came against Jerusalem and encamped against it; and they
        built a siege wall against it all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the city was besieged until the eleventh year of King Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: By the ninth day of the fourth month the famine had become so severe
        in the city that there was no food for the people of the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the city wall was broken through, and all the men of war fled
        at night by way of the gate between two walls, which was by the king\u2019s
        garden, even though the Chaldeans were still encamped all around against
        the city. And the  king went by way of the plain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king, and they overtook
        him in the plains of Jericho. All his army was scattered from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they took the king and brought him up to the king of Babylon at
        Riblah, and they pronounced judgment on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then they killed the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes, put out the
        eyes of Zedekiah, bound him with bronze fetters, and took him to Babylon.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And in the fifth month, on the seventh day of the month (which was 
        the nineteenth year of King Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon), Nebuzaradan
        the captain of the guard, a servant of the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He burned the house of the Lord  and the king\u2019s house; all the
        houses of Jerusalem, that is, all the houses of the great, he burned with
        fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And all the army of the Chaldeans who were  with the captain of the
        guard broke down the walls of Jerusalem all around.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried away captive the
        rest of the people who remained in the city and the defectors who had deserted
        to the king of Babylon, with the rest of the multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the captain of the guard left some of the poor of the land as
        vinedressers and farmers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The bronze pillars that were in the house of the Lord, and the carts
        and the bronze Sea that were in the house of the Lord, the Chaldeans broke
        in pieces, and carried their bronze to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They also took away the pots, the shovels, the trimmers, the spoons,
        and all the bronze utensils with which the priests ministered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The firepans and the basins, the things of solid gold and solid silver,
        the captain of the guard took away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The two pillars, one Sea, and the carts, which Solomon had made for
        the house of the Lord, the bronze of all these articles was beyond measure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The height of one pillar was eighteen cubits, and the capital on it
        was of bronze. The height of the capital was three cubits, and the network
        and pomegranates all around the capital were all of bronze. The second pillar
        was the same, with a network.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the captain of the guard took Seraiah the chief priest, Zephaniah
        the second priest, and the three doorkeepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He also took out of the city an officer who had charge of the men
        of war, five men of the king\u2019s close associates who were found in the
        city, the chief recruiting officer of the army, who mustered the people of
        the land, and sixty men of the people of the land who  were found in the
        city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Nebuzaradan, captain of the guard, took these and brought them
        to the king of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Gedaliah Made Governor of Judah'
      title: Gedaliah Made Governor of Judah
      number: 21
      content: Then the king of Babylon struck them and put them to death at Riblah
        in the land of Hamath. Thus Judah was carried away captive from its own land.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then he made Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, governor
        over the people who remained in the land of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon had left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now when all the captains of the armies, they and their men, heard
        that the king of Babylon had made Gedaliah governor, they came to Gedaliah
        at Mizpah\u2014Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, Johanan the son of Careah, Seraiah
        the son of Tanhumeth the Netophathite, and Jaazaniah the son of a Maachathite,
        they and their men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Gedaliah took an oath before them and their men, and said to
        them, \u201CDo not be afraid of the servants of the Chaldeans. Dwell in the
        land and serve the king of Babylon, and it shall be well with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But it happened in the seventh month that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah,
        the son of Elishama, of the royal family, came with ten men and struck and
        killed Gedaliah, the Jews, as well as the Chaldeans who were with him at
        Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jehoiachin Released from Prison'
      title: Jehoiachin Released from Prison
      number: 26
      content: And all the people, small and great, and the captains of the armies,
        arose and went to Egypt; for they were afraid of the Chaldeans.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the thirty-seventh year of the captivity of
        Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the twelfth month, on the twenty-seventh day
        of the month, that Evil-Merodach king of Babylon, in the year that he began
        to reign, released Jehoiachin king of Judah from prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He spoke kindly to him, and gave him a more prominent seat than those
        of the kings who were with him in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Jehoiachin changed from his prison garments, and he ate bread
        regularly before the king all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And as for his provisions, there  was a regular ration given him by
        the king, a portion for each day, all the days of his life.
      comments: []
